{"type":"user","uuid":"a05976c3-9801-4cdb-b88f-64801e569621","session_id":"1a92230a-3ee9-442f-b7e5-d91466bab0d9","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SLxtHWKJiAnN6QGRf48z4G","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# Dev-Pipeline Session Bootstrap — Tier 2 (Dual Agent)\n   2→\n   3→## Session Context\n   4→\n   5→- **Feature ID**: F-015 | **Session**: F-015-20260320010546 | **Run**: run-20260312-123136\n   6→- **Complexity**: medium | **Retry**: 1 / 3\n   7→- **Previous Status**: N/A (first run) | **Resume From**: null\n   8→- **Init**: true | Artifacts: spec=false plan=false\n   9→\n  10→## Your Mission\n  11→\n  12→You are the **session orchestrator**. Implement Feature F-015: \"Universal Command Natural-Language Routing\".\n  13→\n  14→**CRITICAL**: You MUST NOT exit until ALL work is complete and session-status.json is written. When you spawn subagents, wait for each to finish (run_in_background=false).\n  15→\n  16→**Tier 2 — Dual Agent**: You handle context + planning directly. Then spawn Dev and Reviewer subagents. Spawn Dev and Reviewer agents via the Agent tool.\n  17→\n  18→### Feature Description\n  19→\n  20→为 Telegram 命令系统新增统一自然语言路由层：不仅 `/p`，而是所有命令入口都支持“命令 + 自然语言补充”与“纯自然语言意图”两种输入。系统需先进行意图识别，再映射到对应命令 handler（如 pipeline/planner/bugfix/file/system），避免被固定子命令解析器误判。\n  21→\n  22→该能力需要与现有严格命令协议兼容：显式结构化参数优先、自然语言作为增强层；当语义冲突或置信度不足时，返回候选动作与确认提示，保证可控与可解释。\n  23→\n  24→### Acceptance Criteria\n  25→\n  26→- 所有核心命令入口（如 /pipeline、/planner、/bugfix、文件与系统命令）都可接受自然语言补充输入\n  27→- 用户发送纯自然语言请求时，系统可识别意图并路由到正确命令链路（或要求确认）\n  28→- 显式结构化参数优先于自然语言推断，现有严格子命令行为不回归\n  29→- 语义冲突或低置信度场景会返回候选动作与修正建议，而非直接报未知子命令\n  30→- 新增意图路由测试矩阵，覆盖多命令类别、歧义输入与回退路径\n  31→\n  32→### Dependencies (Already Completed)\n  33→\n  34→- F-002 - Telegram Pipeline Command Router (completed)\n  35→- F-011 - AI CLI Proxy (completed)\n  36→\n  37→### App Global Context\n  38→\n  39→- **design_system**: Telegram command UX with structured message templates\n  40→- **language**: TypeScript\n  41→- **tech_stack**: Node.js + Express + Telegraf + JSON state files + Shell/Python dev-pipeline\n  42→- **testing_strategy**: Jest (unit + integration)\n  43→\n  44→## PrizmKit Directory Convention\n  45→\n  46→```\n  47→.prizmkit/specs/015-universal-command-natural-language-routing/context-snapshot.md  ← written by you, read by Dev + Reviewer\n  48→.prizmkit/specs/015-universal-command-natural-language-routing/plan.md              ← includes Tasks section\n  49→```\n  50→\n  51→**`context-snapshot.md`** is the shared knowledge base. You write it once; Dev and Reviewer read it instead of re-scanning individual files.\n  52→\n  53→---\n  54→\n  55→## Subagent Timeout Recovery\n  56→\n  57→If a subagent times out:\n  58→1. `ls .prizmkit/specs/015-universal-command-natural-language-routing/` — check what exists\n  59→2. Re-spawn with: `\"Read .prizmkit/specs/015-universal-command-natural-language-routing/context-snapshot.md for full context. Do NOT re-read individual source files.\"` + only remaining steps + `model: \"lite\"`\n  60→3. Max 2 retries. After 2 failures, complete the work yourself.\n  61→\n  62→---\n  63→\n  64→## Execution\n  65→\n  66→### Phase 0: SKIP (already initialized)\n  67→\n  68→\n  69→### Phase 1: Build Context Snapshot (you, the orchestrator)\n  70→\n  71→```bash\n  72→ls .prizmkit/specs/015-universal-command-natural-language-routing/context-snapshot.md 2>/dev/null && echo \"EXISTS\" || echo \"MISSING\"\n  73→```\n  74→\n  75→If MISSING — build it now:\n  76→1. Read `.prizm-docs/root.prizm` and relevant L1/L2 prizm docs\n  77→2. Scan `src/` for files related to this feature; read each one\n  78→3. Write `.prizmkit/specs/015-universal-command-natural-language-routing/context-snapshot.md`:\n  79→   - **Section 1 — Feature Brief**: feature description + acceptance criteria (copy from above)\n  80→   - **Section 2 — Project Structure**: relevant `ls src/` output\n  81→   - **Section 3 — Prizm Context**: full content of root.prizm and relevan