{"type":"assistant","uuid":"11207162-d6c3-4374-a433-b595176c5eb8","session_id":"1a92230a-3ee9-442f-b7e5-d91466bab0d9","message":{"id":"11207162-d6c3-4374-a433-b595176c5eb8","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. Now let me provide the comprehensive response:\n\n---\n\n## Summary: F-015 Feature Search Results\n\nI've completed a thorough scan of the PrizmClaw codebase for feature F-015 (Universal Command Natural-Language Routing). Here are my findings:\n\n### 1. KEY FILE LIST WITH PURPOSE\n\n#### Core Command Routing Infrastructure\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/index.js` — Entry point: `routeCommand()` orchestration, permission checks, handler dispatch (194 lines)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/parser.js` — Slash command tokenization, subcommand extraction, options parsing (95 lines)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/registry.js` — Command metadata registration, lookup, alias mapping (221 lines)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/validator.js` — Parameter validation, type checking, normalization (224 lines)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/formatter.js` — Error formatting, response templates, suggestions\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/help.js` — Dynamic help text generation\n\n#### Command Handlers (30 total)\n**Pipeline/Bugfix/Planner Types:**\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` — /pipeline run/status/logs/stop/force-unlock orchestration\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/handlers/bugfix.js` — /bugfix shortcut (delegates to pipeline with type=bugfix)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/handlers/planner.js` — /planner command facade (delegates to pipeline with type=planner)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js` — /plan command for dev pipeline interaction\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/handlers/commit.js` — /commit workflow\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/handlers/commits.js` — /commits log\n\n**File Management Commands:**\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/handlers/ls.js`, `cat.js`, `tree.js`, `find.js`, `head.js`, `tail.js`, `cd.js`, `download.js`, `upload.js`\n\n**System Commands:**\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/handlers/ps.js`, `sysinfo.js`, `kill.js`, `monitor.js`, `stop.js`\n\n**Session/Workflow Commands:**\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/handlers/history.js`, `alias.js`, `sessions.js`, `cron.js`, `watch.js`, `jobs.js`\n\n**Utility Commands:**\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js`, `logs.js`, `audit.js`, `more.js`\n\n#### Bootstrap/Entry\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/telegram.js` — Bot initialization, command registration entry point\n\n---\n\n### 2. PRIZM DOCS TO READ BEFORE EDITS\n\n**L0 Root:**\n- `.prizm-docs/root.prizm` — Project map, module index, top rules\n\n**L1 Modules (related):**\n- `.prizm-docs/bot.prizm` — Bot module overview\n  - Points to L2 subdir: `.prizm-docs/bot/commands.prizm`\n- `.prizm-docs/services.prizm` — Business logic services (needed for routing to handlers)\n- `.prizm-docs/security.prizm` — Permission/authorization integration\n- `.prizm-docs/utils.prizm` — Utilities (logging, markdown formatting)\n\n**L2 Details (critical):**\n- `.prizm-docs/bot/commands.prizm` — Full command routing architecture, handler patterns, TRAPS on permission checks and alias resolution\n\n**Key Existing Patterns from docs:**\n- Permission chain: `routeCommand()` enforces allowlist → role checks → handler invocation\n- Handler contract: every handler exports `<name>Meta` + `handle<Name>()` function pair\n- Registration coupling: handlers only active when `registerPipelineCommands()` wires meta+handler in telegram bootstrap\n- Parser behavior: first non-option token becomes subcommand candidate; validator remaps for commands without declared subcommands\n\n---\n\n### 3. EXISTING INTENT/NL PARSING UTILITIES & PATTERNS\n\n**No dedicated NL parsing utilities exist yet** — F-015 is the first to introduce intent routing.\n\n**Existing confidence/candidate patterns found in:**\n1. **Confirmation Manager** (`src/security/confirmation-manager.js`): manages candidate actions, confirmation flows, scoring/ranking logic for security decisions\n   - Uses `candidate` and `confidence` vocabulary\n   - Provides confirmation/denial patterns that F-015 can reuse\n\n2. **Permission Guard** (`src/security/permission-guard.js`): role-based authorization with score-based matching\n   - Could inform intent confidence levels (e.g., higher confidence if user role matches)\n\n3. **Command Executor Service** (`src/services/command-executor-service.js`): output pagination and error recovery patterns\n   - References `score`, `match`, `probability` in error fallback logic\n\n4. **Alert Manager Service** (`src/services/alert-manager-service.js`): scoring/ranking alerts, priority matching\n   - Pattern: `score(candidate) → ranking → confidence threshold`\n\n**Reusable patterns for NL routing:**\n- Candidate action generation (from confirmation-manager)\n- Confidence scoring (from alert-manager)\n- Fallback/suggestion flow (from formatter.js: `suggestion` field in errors)\n\n---\n\n### 4. TEST FILES FOR REFERENCE\n\n**Core command tests:**\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/bot/commands/parser.test.js` — Parser test patterns (80+ lines)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/bot/commands/validator.test.js`\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/bot/commands/registry.test.js`\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/bot/commands/formatter.test.js`\n\n**Integration tests:**\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/integration/f002-command-router.integration.test.js` — Full routing flow test (68+ lines)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/integration/f002-user-stories.integration.test.js`\n\n**Handler-specific tests:**\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/bot/commands/handlers/*.test.js` — 25+ handler tests (pipeline, bugfix, commit, file ops, system ops)\n\n---\n\n### 5. ARCHITECTURE SNAPSHOT\n\n**Current Flow (command-driven):**\n```\nTelegram Message (text=\"/pipeline run my-feature\")\n  ↓\nparseCommand() → {command: 'pipeline', subcommand: 'run', args: ['my-feature'], ...}\n  ↓\nregistry.getCommand('pipeline') → CommandEntry{meta, handler}\n  ↓\nPermission + Role Check → validateCommand() → Normalization\n  ↓\nhandler(handlerContext) [e.g., handlePipeline()]\n```\n\n**Required Enhancement for F-015 (NL routing):**\n- Add NL intent detection layer BEFORE or AFTER parse\n- Generate candidate commands with confidence scores\n- Return ambiguous cases with suggestions instead of \"unknown command\"\n\n**Entry points that need NL routing:**\n1. `/pipeline` + NL suffix → route to pipeline control\n2. `/planner` + NL suffix → route to planner control\n3. `/bugfix` + NL suffix → route to bugfix control\n4. File commands (`/ls`, `/cat`, `/find`) + NL modifiers → refine file operations\n5. System commands (`/ps`, `/kill`) + NL context → interpret intent\n6. Pure NL (non-slash) → detect intent, confirm, or fallback\n\n---\n\n### 6. NOTES FOR IMPLEMENTATION\n\n**From bot/commands.prizm TRAPS section:**\n- Handler registration must happen at bootstrap; missing a meta/handler pair breaks routing\n- Permission chain is critical security gate — bypass causes inconsistent behavior\n- Alias resolution happens BEFORE parse; avoid hard-coding command names downstream\n- Long output must be paginated; raw output exceeds Telegram message limits\n\n**Dependencies you'll need:**\n- `src/security/permission-guard.js` — for confidence levels based on user role\n- `src/security/confirmation-manager.js` — for candidate action patterns\n- `src/services/command-executor-service.js` — for output handling\n- `src/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js` — for Telegram-safe response formatting\n\n**Test coverage needed:**\n- Intent detection accuracy matrix (multiple command types, ambiguous inputs)\n- Confidence scoring validation\n- Fallback/suggestion generation\n- End-to-end routing (NL → parse → validate → handler)\n- Permission integration (ensure NL doesn't bypass security checks)\n\n---\n\nThis architecture is ready for F-015 implementation. The parser/validator/router foundation is solid; you'll be layering an intent detection + candidate scoring system on top."}],"model":"gpt-5.3-codex","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":55304,"output_tokens":2448,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_pRmaLUV6ETZe0r0My8gPv5G8","__timestamp":"2026-03-19T17:08:31.877Z","_requestId":"261f0390879c473391691a62bef865bb"}
