{"type":"user","uuid":"2eed7ed0-0538-4ec8-b614-43c5dd573c62","session_id":"1a92230a-3ee9-442f-b7e5-d91466bab0d9","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EP5dyvDVk3PfVZusfEX3Ar","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→---\n   2→name: prizm-dev-team-dev\n   3→description: PrizmKit-integrated module implementer (multi-instance). Follows /prizmkit-implement workflow with TDD, marks tasks [x] in plan.md Tasks section, works within assigned Git worktrees. Use when implementing specific feature modules.\n   4→tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TaskCreate, TaskGet, TaskUpdate, TaskList, SendMessage\n   5→model: inherit\n   6→skills: prizmkit-implement, prizmkit-prizm-docs\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→你是 **Dev Agent**，PrizmKit-integrated Multi-Agent 软件开发协作团队的模块实现者。\n  10→\n  11→### 核心身份\n  12→\n  13→你是团队的\"建筑工人\"——严格按图纸施工，使用 PrizmKit 的 implement 工作流作为执行引擎，专注于：\n  14→- 按照 plan.md Tasks section 和接口设计逐任务实现功能模块\n  15→- 遵循 TDD 方式开发（测试先行）\n  16→- 完成后立即标记 plan.md Tasks section 中的 `[x]`\n  17→- 产出代码和单元测试\n  18→\n  19→### 项目上下文\n  20→\n  21→项目文档在 `.prizm-docs/`。实现前先读 `context-snapshot.md`（若存在于 `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/`），其 Section 3 含 Prizm Context、Section 4 含源文件，无需再读 `.prizm-docs/` 或原始源文件。若 snapshot 不存在，则读 `root.prizm` 了解规则和已知陷阱（TRAPS），修改某模块时读该模块的文档。\n  22→\n  23→### 制品路径\n  24→\n  25→| 路径 | 用途 |\n  26→|------|------|\n  27→| `.prizm-docs/` | 项目知识层 — 规则、模式、已知陷阱 |\n  28→| `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` | 功能制品 — spec.md / plan.md（含 Tasks section） |\n  29→\n  30→### 必须做 (MUST)\n  31→\n  32→1. 按照分配的任务和 plan.md 中的接口设计实现功能模块\n  33→2. 遵循 TDD 方式：先写测试，再实现，再验证\n  34→3. 产出的代码必须通过本模块的单元测试\n  35→4. 发现接口设计歧义时，立即上报给 Orchestrator（不自行假设）\n  36→5. 遵循 `/prizmkit-implement` 工作流：读取 plan.md（含 Tasks section）+ spec.md，逐任务实现\n  37→6. 每个任务完成后**立即**标记 plan.md Tasks section 中的 `[x]`（不批量标记）\n  38→7. 实现前读取 TRAPS 段避免已知陷阱：优先从 `context-snapshot.md` Section 3 获取，若 snapshot 不存在则读 `.prizm-docs/`\n  39→8. 检查点任务须验证构建通过和测试通过后才能继续下一阶段\n  40→9. 顺序任务按序执行，失败则停止；并行 `[P]` 任务可继续\n  41→10. 新建子模块时，生成对应的 `.prizm-docs/` L2 文档\n  42→\n  43→### 绝不做 (NEVER)\n  44→\n  45→- 不修改 plan.md 中的接口设计（修改需通过 Orchestrator）\n  46→- 不修改其他 Dev Agent 负责的模块代码\n  47→- 不进行集成测试（Reviewer 的职责）\n  48→- **不执行任何 git 操作**（git commit / git add / git reset / git push 均禁止 — 由 Orchestrator 通过 /prizmkit-committer 统一提交）\n  49→- 不修改 `.prizmkit/specs/` 中除 `plan.md`（标记 Tasks section [x]）以外的任何文件\n  50→- 不为 bug 修复创建新的文档条目；bug 修复是现有功能的完善，应更新原始功能的文档\n  51→- 不使用 TaskCreate/TaskUpdate 创建或修改 Orchestrator 层的任务（Task 工具仅用于内部进度追踪，且任务 ID 在各 agent 子会话中互不共享）\n  52→\n  53→### 行为规则\n  54→\n  55→```\n  56→DEV-01: 实现必须严格符合 plan.md 中定义的接口设计\n  57→DEV-02: 每个公开 API/函数必须有对应的单元测试\n  58→DEV-03: 发现接口设计歧义时，不得自行假设，必须上报\n  59→DEV-04: 任务完成后必须运行全部本模块测试\n  60→DEV-05: 代码提交信息遵循 Conventional Commits 格式（仅供参考，实际提交由 Orchestrator 执行）\n  61→DEV-06: 不得引入未在任务描述中声明的外部依赖\n  62→DEV-07: 遵循 /prizmkit-implement 工作流\n  63→DEV-08: 每个任务完成后立即标记 plan.md Tasks section [x]\n  64→DEV-09: TDD：先写测试 → 再实现 → 再验证\n  65→DEV-10: 实现每个模块前必须读取 TRAPS 段：优先从 context-snapshot.md Section 3 获取，无 snapshot 时读 .prizm-docs/\n  66→DEV-11: 检查点任务必须验证构建通过和测试通过\n  67→DEV-12: 新建子模块时生成 L2 .prizm-docs/ 文档\n  68→DEV-13: 禁止执行任何 git 命令（git add/commit/reset/push 全部禁止）\n  69→DEV-14: 若 `npm test` 中存在 pre-existing 失败，不得忽略——必须在 COMPLETION_SIGNAL 中明确列出，由 Orchestrator 决策\n  70→```\n  71→\n  72→### 工作流程\n  73→\n  74→1. 接收任务分配\n  75→2. 读取 `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/context-snapshot.md`（若存在）——Section 3 含 Prizm Context，Section 4 含源文件。若 snapshot 不存在，则读取 `.prizm-docs/root.prizm` 和相关模块文档\n  76→3. 读取 `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` 中的 `plan.md`（含 Tasks section）、`spec.md`\n  77→4. 对每个分配的任务，按 plan.md Tasks 顺序执行：\n  78→   a. 从 context-snapshot.md 获取目标文件上下文和 TRAPS（若无 snapshot 则读取目标文件模块的文档）\n  79→   b. TDD：基于验收标准编写测试 → 实现功能代码 → 运行测试验证\n  80→   c. 在 plan.md Tasks section 中标记该任务为 `[x]`\n  81→   d. 发送 STATUS_UPDATE 给 Orchestrator\n  82→5. 如遇检查点任务，验证构建通过和测试通过后才继续\n  83→6. 遇到接口设计歧义，发送 ESCALATION（不自行假设）\n  84→7. 如新建了子模块，生成对应 `.prizm-docs/` L2 文档\n  85→8. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL\n  86→\n  87→### 异常处理\n  88→\n  89→| 场景 | 策略 |\n  90→|------|------|\n  91→| 接口设计歧义 | 标记 BLOCKED → ESCALATION → 等待 Orchestrator 裁定 |\n  92→| 单元测试失败 | 最多重试修复 3 次 → 仍失败则 ISSUE_REPORT |\n  93→| 外部依赖不可用 | 使用 Mock → 标注说明 |\n  94→| 任务超出预估 | ESCALATION → 建议 Orchestrator 拆分任务 |\n  95→\n  96→### 通信规则\n  97→\n  98→允许 Agent 之间直接通信，但关键消息和结论必须通知 Orchestrator。\n  99→- 发送 STATUS_UPDATE 汇报每个子任务完成\n 100→- 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL 标志所有任务完成\n 101→- 发送 ESCALATION 上报接口歧义或任务阻塞\n 102→- 接收 TASK_ASSIGNMENT 获取分配的工作\n 103→\n 104→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_ytOeuPPPaoMyUkPYR8DqfePP","__timestamp":"2026-03-19T17:12:53.947Z","_requestId":"261f0390879c473391691a62bef865bb"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"cecea75a-06b2-48b1-853d-1a982e654c38","session_id":"1a92230a-3ee9-442f-b7e5-d91466bab0d9","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FJTmxuTTfQMVFtPrpuzLpa","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-015 Context Snapshot — Universal Command Natural-Language Routing\n   2→\n   3→## Section 1 — Feature Brief\n   4→\n   5→### Feature Description\n   6→\n   7→为 Telegram 命令系统新增统一自然语言路由层：不仅 `/p`，而是所有命令入口都支持“命令 + 自然语言补充”与“纯自然语言意图”两种输入。系统需先进行意图识别，再映射到对应命令 handler（如 pipeline/planner/bugfix/file/system），避免被固定子命令解析器误判。\n   8→\n   9→该能力需要与现有严格命令协议兼容：显式结构化参数优先、自然语言作为增强层；当语义冲突或置信度不足时，返回候选动作与确认提示，保证可控与可解释。\n  10→\n  11→### Acceptance Criteria\n  12→\n  13→- 所有核心命令入口（如 /pipeline、/planner、/bugfix、文件与系统命令）都可接受自然语言补充输入\n  14→- 用户发送纯自然语言请求时，系统可识别意图并路由到正确命令链路（或要求确认）\n  15→- 显式结构化参数优先于自然语言推断，现有严格子命令行为不回归\n  16→- 语义冲突或低置信度场景会返回候选动作与修正建议，而非直接报未知子命令\n  17→- 新增意图路由测试矩阵，覆盖多命令类别、歧义输入与回退路径\n  18→\n  19→## Section 2 — Project Structure\n  20→\n  21→### `ls src`\n  22→\n  23→```text\n  24→adapters\n  25→bot\n  26→config.js\n  27→http\n  28→index.js\n  29→pipeline-infra\n  30→routes\n  31→security\n  32→services\n  33→utils\n  34→```\n  35→\n  36→### `ls src/bot`\n  37→\n  38→```text\n  39→commands\n  40→telegram.js\n  41→```\n  42→\n  43→### `ls src/bot/commands`\n  44→\n  45→```text\n  46→formatter.js\n  47→handlers\n  48→help.js\n  49→index.js\n  50→parser.js\n  51→registry.js\n  52→validator.js\n  53→```\n  54→\n  55→### `ls src/bot/commands/handlers`\n  56→\n  57→```text\n  58→alias.js\n  59→audit.js\n  60→bugfix.js\n  61→cat.js\n  62→cd.js\n  63→commit.js\n  64→commits.js\n  65→cron.js\n  66→download.js\n  67→find.js\n  68→head.js\n  69→history.js\n  70→jobs.js\n  71→kill.js\n  72→logs.js\n  73→ls.js\n  74→monitor.js\n  75→more.js\n  76→pipeline.js\n  77→plan.js\n  78→planner.js\n  79→ps.js\n  80→sessions.js\n  81→status.js\n  82→stop.js\n  83→sysinfo.js\n  84→tail.js\n  85→tree.js\n  86→upload.js\n  87→watch.js\n  88→```\n  89→\n  90→### `ls tests/bot/commands`\n  91→\n  92→```text\n  93→fixtures\n  94→formatter.test.js\n  95→handlers\n  96→parser.test.js\n  97→registry.test.js\n  98→validator.test.js\n  99→```\n 100→\n 101→### `ls tests/integration`\n 102→\n 103→```text\n 104→ai-cli-error-handling.test.js\n 105→ai-cli-heartbeat.test.js\n 106→ai-cli-markdownv2.test.js\n 107→ai-cli-telegram.test.js\n 108→commit-flow.test.js\n 109→commit-validation.test.js\n 110→commit-workflow.test.js\n 111→e2e-main-chain.test.js\n 112→f001-infrastructure.integration.test.js\n 113→f001-user-stories.integration.test.js\n 114→f002-command-router.integration.test.js\n 115→f002-user-stories.integration.test.js\n 116→f003-plan-ingestion.integration.test.js\n 117→f004-extended.integration.test.js\n 118→f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js\n 119→f005-extended.integration.test.js\n 120→f005-status-and-logs.integration.test.js\n 121→f009-command-executor.integration.test.js\n 122→f010-file-manager.test.js\n 123→f011-comprehensive.test.js\n 124→f012-system-monitor.test.js\n 125→f014-file-watchers.test.js\n 126→f014-scheduled-tasks.test.js\n 127→plan-version-flow.test.js\n 128→security-extended.test.js\n 129→security-flow.test.js\n 130→```\n 131→\n 132→## Section 3 — Prizm Context\n 133→\n 134→### .prizm-docs/root.prizm\n 135→\n 136→```text\n 137→PRIZM_VERSION: 2\n 138→PROJECT: PrizmClaw\n 139→LANG: JavaScript\n 140→FRAMEWORK: Node.js ES2022 + TypeScript\n 141→TECH_STACK: Express, Telegraf, Zod, Pino logging\n 142→BUILD: npm start (node src/index.js)\n 143→TEST: npm test\n 144→ENTRY: src/index.js\n 145→MODULE_INDEX:\n 146→- bot -> .prizm-docs/bot.prizm\n 147→- services -> .prizm-docs/services.prizm\n 148→- pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/pipeline-infra.prizm\n 149→- security -> .prizm-docs/security.prizm\n 150→- utils -> .prizm-docs/utils.prizm\n 151→- http -> .prizm-docs/http.prizm\n 152→- routes -> .prizm-docs/routes.prizm\n 153→- adapters -> .prizm-docs/adapters.prizm\n 154→RULES:\n 155→- Progressive loading: read L0 on session start, L1 on module task, L2 before file edits\n 156→- Keep .prizm docs KEY: value with dash lists only; avoid prose and markdown headers\n 157→- Use append-only updates for DECISIONS and CHANGELOG sections\n 158→- Feature development updates .prizm-docs; bug-fix-only logic changes can skip doc updates\n 159→- Keep hard size limits: root<=4KB, L1<=3KB, L2<=5KB\n 160→- Before commit: run /prizmkit-retrospective then /prizmkit-committer\n 161→- Commit messages use Conventional Commits; bug fixes use fix(scope): description\n 162→- Prefer fast path for clear bug/config/refactor tasks; full workflow for multi-module feature changes\n 163→UPDATED: 2026-03-19\n 164→```\n 165→\n 166→### .prizm-docs/bot.prizm\n 167→\n 168→```text\n 169→MODULE: bot\n 170→FILES: 37 total\n 171→RESPONSIBILITY: Telegram bot command routing and message handling\n 172→SUBDIRS:\n 173→- commands -> .prizm-docs/bot/commands.prizm\n 174→KEY_FILES:\n 175→- src/bot/telegram.js: bot bootstrap, command registration, text/document handlers, stream/file reply orchestration\n 176→- src/bot/commands/index.js: command router entry and middleware exports\n 177→- src/bot/commands/registry.js: command metadata registry and alias map\n 178→- src/bot/commands/parser.js: slash command tokenization and option parsing\n 179→- src/bot/commands/validator.js: parameter/subcommand validation and normalization\n 180→- src/bot/commands/help.js: dynamic help text generator from registry\n 181→- src/bot/commands/formatter.js: user-facing command error formatting\n 182→INTERFACES:\n 183→- createTelegramBot(): Promise<Telegraf>\n 184→- routeCommand(ctx): Promise<boolean>\n 185→- createCommandMiddleware(): (ctx,next)=>Promise<void>\n 186→- registerCommand(meta, handler): void\n 187→- getCommand(name): CommandEntry|null\n 188→- parseCommand(text, aliasMap?): ParsedCommand|null\n 189→- validateCommand(parsed, meta): ValidationResult\n 190→- generateHelp(commandName?): string\n 191→DEPENDENCIES:\n 192→- telegraf: Telegram bot framework and update context\n 193→- src/security/*: allowlist, roles, permission checks\n 194→- src/services/*: chat, ai-cli, command executor, audit, scheduling\n 195→- src/pipeline-infra/*: plan ingestion and pipeline control integration\n 196→- src/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js: Telegram-safe rendering\n 197→UPDATED: 2026-03-19\n 198→```\n 199→\n 200→### .prizm-docs/bot/commands.prizm\n 201→\n 202→```text\n 203→MODULE: bot/commands\n 204→FILES: src/bot/commands/**/*.js (36 files)\n 205→KEY_FILES:\n 206→- src/bot/commands/index.js: routeCommand orchestration and handler context assembly\n 207→- src/bot/commands/registry.js: command registration, alias mapping, help source of truth\n 208→- src/bot/commands/parser.js: parses /cmd subcommand args --key=value flags\n 209→- src/bot/commands/validator.js: schema-style validation and normalized params output\n 210→- src/bot/commands/formatter.js: standardized command error responses\n 211→- src/bot/commands/help.js: general and per-command usage generation\n 212→- src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js: feature pipeline launch/status/logs control\n 213→- src/bot/commands/handlers/bugfix.js: bugfix pipeline command surface\n 214→- src/bot/commands/handlers/commit.js: commit workflow command facade\n 215→- src/bot/commands/handlers/cron.js: scheduled task create/list/pause/resume/delete\n 216→DEPENDENCIES:\n 217→- imports: src/security/guard.js: base user authorization gate\n 218→- imports: src/security/permission-guard.js: role based command authorization\n 219→- imports: src/services/audit-log-service.js: denied/critical action audit trail\n 220→- imports: src/services/command-executor-service.js: /exec command execution pipeline\n 221→- imports: src/services/output-pager-service.js: paginated long output and /more follow-up\n 222→- imports: src/services/*-service.js: pipeline, monitor, session, alias, watcher integrations\n 223→TRAPS:\n 224→- handler contract pattern: every handler exports <name>Meta and handle<Name>; missing pair breaks registration\n 225→- registration coupling: handlers are active only when registerPipelineCommands() wires meta+handler in telegram bootstrap\n 226→- parser behavior: first non-option token becomes subcommand candidate; validator remaps for commands without declared subcommands\n 227→- permission chain: routeCommand enforces allowlist and role checks before handler invocation; bypass causes inconsistent security behavior\n 228→- long output flow: handlers should paginate/store extra pages; sending full raw output can exceed Telegram limits\n 229→- alias flow: user aliases resolve before parse/validate; avoid hard-coding command names in downstream logic\n 230→CHANGELOG:\n 231→- 2026-03-19 | add: initial L2 documentation for bot commands routing and handler patterns\n 232→UPDATED: 2026-03-19\n 233→```\n 234→\n 235→### .prizm-docs/services.prizm\n 236→\n 237→```text\n 238→MODULE: services\n 239→FILES: 26 total\n 240→RESPONSIBILITY: Business logic services for chat bridge, git/commit workflow, pipeline control, monitoring, sessions, and scheduling\n 241→KEY_FILES:\n 242→- src/services/chat-service.js: session prompt assembly and CodeBuddy adapter invocation\n 243→- src/services/ai-cli-service.js: process-tracked AI CLI execution with heartbeat and interrupt\n 244→- src/services/command-executor-service.js: secured shell execution, confirmation flow, output pagination\n 245→- src/services/pipeline-controller.js: start/stop/retry/status/logs orchestration with locks/state\n 246→- src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js: JSON schema validation, versioning, active plan registry\n 247→- src/services/session-context-service.js: session lifecycle, persistence, timeout cleanup\n 248→- src/services/scheduled-task-service.js: cron/one-time task scheduling and callback dispatch\n 249→- src/services/file-watcher-service.js: fs.watch-based watcher registry and notification debounce\n 250→INTERFACES:\n 251→- chatWithSession(params): Promise<string>\n 252→- executeAiCli(options): Promise<AiCliExecutionResult>\n 253→- executeCommand(options): Promise<CommandResult>\n 254→- createPipelineController(options): PipelineController\n 255→- createPipelineControlService(options): PipelineControlService\n 256→- createPlanIngestionService(config): PlanIngestionService\n 257→- createCommitService(options): CommitService\n 258→- createStatusAggregator(options): StatusAggregator\n 259→- createLogPager(options): LogPager\n 260→DEPENDENCIES:\n 261→- simple-git: git status and commit operations\n 262→- ajv: plan schema compilation/validation\n 263→- croner: cron expression scheduling runtime\n 264→- node:child_process/fs/path/events: process and state I/O primitives\n 265→- src/pipeline-infra/*: script execution, config, lock/state/path policies\n 266→- src/security/*: permission, confirmation, blacklist/high-risk checks\n 267→UPDATED: 2026-03-19\n 268→```\n 269→\n 270→### .prizm-docs/security.prizm\n 271→\n 272→```text\n 273→MODULE: security\n 274→FILES: 6\n 275→RESPONSIBILITY: Authentication checks, role-based command permissions, parameter sanitization, and high-risk confirmation controls\n 276→KEY_FILES:\n 277→- src/security/guard.js: allowed user gate and prompt input sanitization\n 278→- src/security/permission-guard.js: role hierarchy and per-command permission rules\n 279→- src/security/param-sanitizer.js: dangerous pattern detection and safe param normalization\n 280→- src/security/confirmation-manager.js: pending confirmation lifecycle with timeout\n 281→- src/security/system-guard.js: system-exec enablement, allowlist, blacklist, high-risk keyword checks\n 282→- src/security/index.js: module export hub\n 283→INTERFACES:\n 284→- isAllowedUser(userId): boolean\n 285→- sanitizeInput(input): string\n 286→- getUserRole(userId): 'admin'|'operator'|'viewer'\n 287→- checkCommandPermission(userId, command): PermissionResult\n 288→- sanitizeParam(input, options?): SanitizedParamResult\n 289→- validatePath(inputPath, allowedRoots): PathValidationResult\n 290→- createConfirmation(userId, action, params, timeoutMs?): ConfirmationPrompt\n 291→- confirmAction(confirmId, userId): ConfirmResult\n 292→- checkCommandBlacklist(command, blacklist): BlacklistCheckResult\n 293→- detectHighRiskKeywords(command, keywords): HighRiskCheckResult\n 294→UPDATED: 2026-03-19\n 295→```\n 296→\n 297→### .prizm-docs/utils.prizm\n 298→\n 299→```text\n 300→MODULE: utils\n 301→FILES: 4\n 302→RESPONSIBILITY: Shared utility helpers for logging, file formatting, heartbeat lifecycle, and Telegram MarkdownV2 conversion\n 303→KEY_FILES:\n 304→- src/utils/logger.js: centralized pino logger factory/instance\n 305→- src/utils/file-utils.js: file size/date/content helpers for file manager commands\n 306→- src/utils/heartbeat-manager.js: reusable heartbeat timer and manager abstraction\n 307→- src/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js: markdown escaping and segmentation for Telegram limits\n 308→INTERFACES:\n 309→- logger: pino.Logger\n 310→- formatFileSize(bytes): string\n 311→- formatDate(date): string\n 312→- isBinaryContent(buffer, sampleSize?): boolean\n 313→- startHeartbeat(options): stopFn\n 314→- createHeartbeatManager(): {start,stop,isRunning}\n 315→- escapeMarkdownV2(text): string\n 316→- convertToMarkdownV2(markdown): string\n 317→- splitRespectingCodeBlocks(text, maxLength?): string[]\n 318→DEPENDENCIES:\n 319→- pino: structured logging backend\n 320→- node runtime timers and Buffer APIs\n 321→UPDATED: 2026-03-19\n 322→```\n 323→\n 324→## Section 4 — Existing Source Files\n 325→\n 326→### src/bot/telegram.js (1004 lines)\n 327→\n 328→```js\n 329→import { Telegraf } from 'telegraf';\n 330→import { createReadStream } from 'node:fs';\n 331→import { access, stat } from 'node:fs/promises';\n 332→import os from 'node:os';\n 333→import path from 'node:path';\n 334→import { config } from '../config.js';\n 335→import { logger } from '../utils/logger.js';\n 336→import { isAllowedUser } from '../security/guard.js';\n 337→import { chatWithSession, resetSession } from '../services/chat-service.js';\n 338→import { executeAiCli, interruptAiCli, isAiCliRunning } from '../services/ai-cli-service.js';\n 339→import { captureScreenshot } from '../services/screenshot-service.js';\n 340→import { executeCommand, confirmHighRiskCommand } from '../services/command-executor-service.js';\n 341→import { createPlanIngestionService } from '../services/plan-ingestion-service.js';\n 342→import { loadPipelineInfraConfig } from '../pipeline-infra/config-loader.js';\n 343→import { registerCommand } from './commands/index.js';\n 344→import { routeCommand } from './commands/index.js';\n 345→import { pipelineMeta, handlePipeline } from './commands/handlers/pipeline.js';\n 346→import { bugfixMeta, handleBugfix } from './commands/handlers/bugfix.js';\n 347→import { plannerMeta, handlePlanner } from './commands/handlers/planner.js';\n 348→import { statusMeta, handleStatus } from './commands/handlers/status.js';\n 349→import { logsMeta, handleLogs } from './commands/handlers/logs.js';\n 350→import { stopMeta, handleStop } from './commands/handlers/stop.js';\n 351→import { planMeta, handlePlan } from './commands/handlers/plan.js';\n 352→import { auditMeta, handleAudit } from './commands/handlers/audit.js';\n 353→import { commitMeta, handleCommit } from './commands/handlers/commit.js';\n 354→import { commitsMeta, handleCommits } from './commands/handlers/commits.js';\n 355→// F-009: New command handlers\n 356→import { cdMeta, handleCd } from './commands/handlers/cd.js';\n 357→import { moreMeta, handleMore } from './commands/handlers/more.js';\n 358→// F-010: File Manager command handlers\n 359→import { lsMeta, handleLs } from './commands/handlers/ls.js';\n 360→import { treeMeta, handleTree } from './commands/handlers/tree.js';\n 361→import { catMeta, handleCat } from './commands/handlers/cat.js';\n 362→import { headMeta, handleHead } from './commands/handlers/head.js';\n 363→import { tailMeta, handleTail } from './commands/handlers/tail.js';\n 364→import { findMeta, handleFind } from './commands/handlers/find.js';\n 365→import { uploadMeta, handleUpload } from './commands/handlers/upload.js';\n 366→import { downloadMeta, handleDownload } from './commands/handlers/download.js';\n 367→// F-012: System Monitor command handlers\n 368→import { sysinfoMeta, handleSysinfo } from './commands/handlers/sysinfo.js';\n 369→import { psMeta, handlePs } from './commands/handlers/ps.js';\n 370→import { killMeta, handleKill } from './commands/handlers/kill.js';\n 371→import { monitorMeta, handleMonitor } from './commands/handlers/monitor.js';\n 372→// F-013: Session and Context Manager command handlers\n 373→import { historyMeta, handleHistory } from './commands/handlers/history.js';\n 374→import { aliasMeta, handleAlias } from './commands/handlers/alias.js';\n 375→import { sessionsMeta, handleSessions } from './commands/handlers/sessions.js';\n 376→// F-014: Notification and Scheduled Tasks command handlers\n 377→import { cronMeta, handleCron } from './commands/handlers/cron.js';\n 378→import { jobsMeta, handleJobs } from './commands/handlers/jobs.js';\n 379→import { watchMeta, handleWatch } from './commands/handlers/watch.js';\n 380→import { generateHelp } from './commands/help.js';\n 381→import { sessionStore } from '../services/session-store.js';\n 382→import { sessionContextService } from '../services/session-context-service.js';\n 383→import { aliasStore } from '../services/alias-store.js';\n 384→import { scheduledTaskService } from '../services/scheduled-task-service.js';\n 385→import { fileWatcherService } from '../services/file-watcher-service.js';\n 386→import { convertToMarkdownV2 } from '../utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js';\n 387→import { escapeMarkdownV2 } from '../utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js';\n 388→\n 389→const TELEGRAM_MSG_CHUNK_SIZE = 3800;\n 390→const STREAM_MIN_CHARS = 220;\n 391→const STREAM_FLUSH_INTERVAL_MS = 1200;\n 392→const TYPING_INTERVAL_MS = 3500;\n 393→const PHOTO_EXTENSIONS = new Set(['.png', '.jpg', '.jpeg', '.webp']);\n 394→const DOCUMENT_EXTENSIONS = new Set(['.pdf', '.txt', '.json', '.md', '.csv', '.log']);\n 395→const ALLOWED_FILE_EXTENSIONS = new Set([...PHOTO_EXTENSIONS, ...DOCUMENT_EXTENSIONS]);\n 396→const TELEGRAM_MAX_PHOTO_BYTES = 10 * 1024 * 1024;\n 397→const TELEGRAM_MAX_DOCUMENT_BYTES = 45 * 1024 * 1024;\n 398→const TELEGRAM_HANDLER_TIMEOUT_MS = 10 * 60 * 1000;\n 399→const TMP_DIR = path.resolve(os.tmpdir());\n 400→const HOME_DIR = path.resolve(os.homedir());\n 401→const DESKTOP_DIR = path.join(HOME_DIR, 'Desktop');\n 402→const DOWNLOADS_DIR = path.join(HOME_DIR, 'Downloads');\n 403→const DEFAULT_ALLOWED_FILE_ROOTS = [path.resolve(process.cwd()), DESKTOP_DIR, DOWNLOADS_DIR, TMP_DIR];\n 404→const DEFAULT_FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS = [path.resolve(process.cwd()), DESKTOP_DIR, DOWNLOADS_DIR, TMP_DIR];\n 405→\n 406→function resolveConfiguredDirs(configuredDirs = [], fallbackDirs = []) {\n 407→  const normalized = configuredDirs\n 408→    .map((dir) => String(dir ?? '').trim())\n 409→    .filter(Boolean)\n 410→    .map((dir) => path.resolve(dir));\n 411→\n 412→  if (normalized.length > 0) {\n 413→    return [...new Set(normalized)];\n 414→  }\n 415→\n 416→  return [...new Set(fallbackDirs.map((dir) => path.resolve(String(dir))))];\n 417→}\n 418→\n 419→const ALLOWED_FILE_ROOTS = resolveConfiguredDirs(config.telegramFileAllowedRoots, DEFAULT_ALLOWED_FILE_ROOTS);\n 420→const FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS = resolveConfiguredDirs(config.telegramFileCandidateDirs, DEFAULT_FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS);\n 421→\n 422→function splitMessage(text, chunkSize = TELEGRAM_MSG_CHUNK_SIZE) {\n 423→  const chunks = [];\n 424→  for (let i = 0; i < text.length; i += chunkSize) {\n 425→    chunks.push(text.slice(i, i + chunkSize));\n 426→  }\n 427→  return chunks;\n 428→}\n 429→\n 430→function truncate(text, maxLen) {\n 431→  if (!text) return '';\n 432→  if (text.length <= maxLen) return text;\n 433→  return text.substring(0, maxLen) + '...';\n 434→}\n 435→\n 436→function sanitizeMarkerPath(raw) {\n 437→  return String(raw ?? '')\n 438→    .trim()\n 439→    .replace(/^['\"`]+/, '')\n 440→    .replace(/['\"`]+$/, '');\n 441→}\n 442→\n 443→function extractFileMarkers(text = '') {\n 444→  const fileRefs = [];\n 445→\n 446→  const withSendFileRemoved = text.replace(\n 447→    /(?:^|\\n)\\s*(?:[-*]\\s*)?`?SEND_FILE:([^\\n`]+)`?\\s*(?=\\n|$)/g,\n 448→    (_full, rawRef) => {\n 449→      const ref = sanitizeMarkerPath(rawRef);\n 450→      if (ref) {\n 451→        fileRefs.push(ref);\n 452→      }\n 453→      return '\\n';\n 454→    }\n 455→  );\n 456→\n 457→  const withImageRemoved = withSendFileRemoved.replace(/@image:([^\\s`]+)/g, (_full, rawRef) => {\n 458→    const ref = sanitizeMarkerPath(rawRef);\n 459→    if (ref) {\n 460→      fileRefs.push(ref);\n 461→    }\n 462→    return '';\n 463→  });\n 464→\n 465→  const withBacktickPathRemoved = withImageRemoved.replace(\n 466→    /`((?:\\/[^`\\n\\r]+)+\\.(?:png|jpg|jpeg|webp|pdf|txt|json|md|csv|log))`/gi,\n 467→    (_full, rawRef) => {\n 468→      const ref = sanitizeMarkerPath(rawRef);\n 469→      if (ref) {\n 470→        fileRefs.push(ref);\n 471→      }\n 472→      return '';\n 473→    }\n 474→  );\n 475→\n 476→  const withLabeledPathRemoved = withBacktickPathRemoved.replace(\n 477→    /(?:文件路径|path)\\s*[:：]\\s*((?:\\/[^\\n`\\r]+)+\\.(?:png|jpg|jpeg|webp|pdf|txt|json|md|csv|log))/gi,\n 478→    (_full, rawRef) => {\n 479→      const ref = sanitizeMarkerPath(rawRef);\n 480→      if (ref) {\n 481→        fileRefs.push(ref);\n 482→      }\n 483→      return '';\n 484→    }\n 485→  );\n 486→\n 487→  const withAbsolutePathLineRemoved = withLabeledPathRemoved.replace(\n 488→    /(?:^|\\n)\\s*(?:[-*]\\s*)?((?:\\/[^\\n`\\r]+)+\\.(?:png|jpg|jpeg|webp|pdf|txt|json|md|csv|log))\\s*(?=\\n|$)/gi,\n 489→    (_full, rawRef) => {\n 490→      const ref = sanitizeMarkerPath(rawRef);\n 491→      if (ref) {\n 492→        fileRefs.push(ref);\n 493→      }\n 494→      return '\\n';\n 495→    }\n 496→  );\n 497→\n 498→  return {\n 499→    fileRefs: [...new Set(fileRefs)],\n 500→    cleanedText: withAbsolutePathLineRemoved.replace(/\\n{3,}/g, '\\n\\n').trim()\n 501→  };\n 502→}\n 503→\n 504→function isPathWithinRoot(targetPath, rootPath) {\n 505→  const relative = path.relative(rootPath, targetPath);\n 506→  return relative === '' || (!relative.startsWith('..') && !path.isAbsolute(relative));\n 507→}\n 508→\n 509→function isAllowedFilePath(filePath) {\n 510→  const resolved = path.resolve(filePath);\n 511→  return ALLOWED_FILE_ROOTS.some((root) => isPathWithinRoot(resolved, root));\n 512→}\n 513→\n 514→function buildFileCandidates(normalizedPath) {\n 515→  if (path.isAbsolute(normalizedPath)) {\n 516→    return [normalizedPath];\n 517→  }\n 518→\n 519→  const baseName = path.basename(normalizedPath);\n 520→  const candidates = [\n 521→    path.resolve(process.cwd(), normalizedPath),\n 522→    ...FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS.map((dir) => path.resolve(dir, baseName))\n 523→  ];\n 524→\n 525→  return [...new Set(candidates)];\n 526→}\n 527→\n 528→async function resolveLocalFilePath(fileRef) {\n 529→  const normalized = sanitizeMarkerPath(fileRef);\n 530→  if (!normalized) {\n 531→    return { filePath: null, triedPaths: [], rejectReason: 'empty_path' };\n 532→  }\n 533→\n 534→  if (!path.isAbsolute(normalized)) {\n 535→    return { filePath: null, triedPaths: [], rejectReason: 'relative_path_not_allowed' };\n 536→  }\n 537→\n 538→  const candidates = buildFileCandidates(normalized);\n 539→\n 540→  for (const candidate of candidates) {\n 541→    try {\n 542→      await access(candidate);\n 543→      return { filePath: candidate, triedPaths: candidates };\n 544→    } catch {\n 545→      // ignore\n 546→    }\n 547→  }\n 548→\n 549→  return { filePath: null, triedPaths: candidates, rejectReason: 'not_found' };\n 550→}\n 551→\n 552→async function validateFileForTelegram(filePath) {\n 553→  const resolvedPath = path.resolve(filePath);\n 554→  if (!isAllowedFilePath(resolvedPath)) {\n 555→    return { ok: false, reason: `路径不在允许范围：${resolvedPath}` };\n 556→  }\n 557→\n 558→  const ext = path.extname(resolvedPath).toLowerCase();\n 559→  if (!ALLOWED_FILE_EXTENSIONS.has(ext)) {\n 560→    return { ok: false, reason: `不支持的文件类型：${ext || '(unknown)'}` };\n 561→  }\n 562→\n 563→  const fileStat = await stat(resolvedPath);\n 564→  const isPhoto = PHOTO_EXTENSIONS.has(ext);\n 565→  const maxSize = isPhoto ? TELEGRAM_MAX_PHOTO_BYTES : TELEGRAM_MAX_DOCUMENT_BYTES;\n 566→\n 567→  if (fileStat.size > maxSize) {\n 568→    return {\n 569→      ok: false,\n 570→      reason: `文件过大：${Math.ceil(fileStat.size / 1024 / 1024)}MB，限制 ${Math.floor(maxSize / 1024 / 1024)}MB`\n 571→    };\n 572→  }\n 573→\n 574→  return { ok: true, isPhoto, resolvedPath };\n 575→}\n 576→\n 577→function isTimeoutLikeError(message = '') {\n 578→  const normalized = String(message).toLowerCase();\n 579→  return normalized.includes('timed out') || normalized.includes('etimedout') || normalized.includes('timeout');\n 580→}\n 581→\n 582→function sleep(ms) {\n 583→  return new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\n 584→}\n 585→\n 586→async function sendTelegramFileByType(ctx, filePath, isPhoto) {\n 587→  if (isPhoto) {\n 588→    await ctx.replyWithPhoto({ source: createReadStream(filePath) }, { caption: path.basename(filePath) });\n 589→    return;\n 590→  }\n 591→\n 592→  await ctx.replyWithDocument({ source: createReadStream(filePath), filename: path.basename(filePath) });\n 593→}\n 594→\n 595→async function replyFiles(ctx, fileRefs = []) {\n 596→  const results = [];\n 597→\n 598→  for (const fileRef of fileRefs) {\n 599→    const { filePath, triedPaths, rejectReason } = await resolveLocalFilePath(fileRef);\n 600→    if (!filePath) {\n 601→      const reason = rejectReason || 'not_found';\n 602→      results.push({ fileRef, sent: false, reason, triedPaths });\n 603→      logger.warn({ fileRef, reason, triedPaths }, 'File unavailable for telegram upload');\n 604→      continue;\n 605→    }\n 606→\n 607→    try {\n 608→      const validation = await validateFileForTelegram(filePath);\n 609→      if (!validation.ok) {\n 610→        results.push({ fileRef, sent: false, reason: validation.reason, filePath, triedPaths });\n 611→        logger.warn({ fileRef, filePath, reason: validation.reason }, 'File validation failed for telegram upload');\n 612→        continue;\n 613→      }\n 614→\n 615→      const actualPath = validation.resolvedPath;\n 616→      let sent = false;\n 617→      let lastReason = '';\n 618→\n 619→      for (let attempt = 1; attempt <= 2; attempt += 1) {\n 620→        try {\n 621→          await sendTelegramFileByType(ctx, actualPath, validation.isPhoto);\n 622→          sent = true;\n 623→          logger.info(\n 624→            { fileRef, filePath: actualPath, as: validation.isPhoto ? 'photo' : 'document', attempt },\n 625→            'Telegram file sent'\n 626→          );\n 627→          break;\n 628→        } catch (error) {\n 629→          lastReason = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n 630→          logger.warn(\n 631→            { fileRef, filePath: actualPath, err: lastReason, attempt },\n 632→            'Telegram file send attempt failed'\n 633→          );\n 634→\n 635→          if (attempt < 2 && isTimeoutLikeError(lastReason)) {\n 636→            await sleep(600);\n 637→            continue;\n 638→          }\n 639→\n 640→          break;\n 641→        }\n 642→      }\n 643→\n 644→      if (!sent) {\n 645→        results.push({ fileRef, sent: false, reason: lastReason || 'unknown_error', filePath: actualPath, triedPaths });\n 646→        logger.error({ fileRef, filePath: actualPath, err: lastReason }, 'Failed to send file to telegram');\n 647→        continue;\n 648→      }\n 649→\n 650→      results.push({ fileRef, sent: true, filePath: actualPath, triedPaths });\n 651→    } catch (error) {\n 652→      const reason = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n 653→      results.push({ fileRef, sent: false, reason, filePath, triedPaths });\n 654→      logger.error({ fileRef, filePath, err: reason }, 'Failed to send file to telegram');\n 655→    }\n 656→  }\n 657→\n 658→  return results;\n 659→}\n 660→\n 661→async function safeReply(ctx, text) {\n 662→  try {\n 663→    await ctx.reply(text);\n 664→    return true;\n 665→  } catch (error) {\n 666→    const reason = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n 667→    logger.error({ err: reason }, 'Failed to send telegram text reply');\n 668→    return false;\n 669→  }\n 670→}\n 671→\n 672→async function replyLargeText(ctx, text) {\n 673→  const chunks = splitMessage(text);\n 674→  for (const chunk of chunks) {\n 675→    const ok = await safeReply(ctx, chunk);\n 676→    if (!ok) {\n 677→      break;\n 678→    }\n 679→  }\n 680→}\n 681→\n 682→async function safeEditMessageText(ctx, messageId, text) {\n 683→  const nextText = text && text.trim() ? text : ' ';\n 684→\n 685→  try {\n 686→    await ctx.telegram.editMessageText(ctx.chat.id, messageId, undefined, nextText);\n 687→  } catch (error) {\n 688→    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n 689→    if (message.includes('message is not modified')) {\n 690→      return;\n 691→    }\n 692→    throw error;\n 693→  }\n 694→}\n 695→\n 696→function createEditableStreamPublisher(ctx) {\n 697→  let fullText = '';\n 698→  let renderedText = '';\n 699→  let pendingChars = 0;\n 700→  let lastFlushAt = 0;\n 701→  let flushChain = Promise.resolve();\n 702→  let activeMessage = null;\n 703→  let activeSegmentIndex = 0;\n 704→  let publishedMessageCount = 0;\n 705→\n 706→  async function ensureActiveMessage() {\n 707→    if (activeMessage) {\n 708→      return;\n 709→    }\n 710→    activeMessage = await ctx.reply('处理中...');\n 711→    activeSegmentIndex = 0;\n 712→    publishedMessageCount += 1;\n 713→  }\n 714→\n 715→  async function render(force = false) {\n 716→    const now = Date.now();\n 717→\n 718→    if (!force && pendingChars < STREAM_MIN_CHARS && now - lastFlushAt < STREAM_FLUSH_INTERVAL_MS) {\n 719→      return;\n 720→    }\n 721→\n 722→    if (fullText === renderedText) {\n 723→      pendingChars = 0;\n 724→      return;\n 725→    }\n 726→\n 727→    await ensureActiveMessage();\n 728→\n 729→    const segments = splitMessage(fullText);\n 730→    const targetLastIndex = Math.max(segments.length - 1, 0);\n 731→\n 732→    while (activeSegmentIndex < targetLastIndex) {\n 733→      const text = segments[activeSegmentIndex] ?? ' ';\n 734→      await safeEditMessageText(ctx, activeMessage.message_id, text);\n 735→\n 736→      activeMessage = await ctx.reply('继续输出中...');\n 737→      activeSegmentIndex += 1;\n 738→      publishedMessageCount += 1;\n 739→    }\n 740→\n 741→    const activeText = segments[targetLastIndex] ?? ' ';\n 742→    await safeEditMessageText(ctx, activeMessage.message_id, activeText);\n 743→\n 744→    renderedText = fullText;\n 745→    pendingChars = 0;\n 746→    lastFlushAt = now;\n 747→  }\n 748→\n 749→  function enqueueRender(force = false) {\n 750→    flushChain = flushChain.then(() => render(force));\n 751→  }\n 752→\n 753→  return {\n 754→    push(text) {\n 755→      const appendText = text ?? '';\n 756→      if (!appendText) {\n 757→        return;\n 758→      }\n 759→      fullText += appendText;\n 760→      pendingChars += appendText.length;\n 761→      enqueueRender(false);\n 762→    },\n 763→    setFinalText(text) {\n 764→      fullText = text ?? '';\n 765→      pendingChars = Math.max(pendingChars, STREAM_MIN_CHARS);\n 766→      enqueueRender(true);\n 767→    },\n 768→    async finish() {\n 769→      enqueueRender(true);\n 770→      await flushChain;\n 771→      return {\n 772→        outputLength: renderedText.length,\n 773→        messageCount: publishedMessageCount\n 774→      };\n 775→    }\n 776→  };\n 777→}\n 778→\n 779→function buildSessionId(ctx) {\n 780→  return String(ctx.chat.id);\n 781→}\n 782→\n 783→function ensureAllowed(ctx) {\n 784→  const userId = ctx.from?.id;\n 785→  if (!isAllowedUser(userId)) {\n 786→    throw new Error('当前账号未被授权使用该机器人。');\n 787→  }\n 788→}\n 789→\n 790→/**\n 791→ * Register all pipeline-related commands.\n 792→ */\n 793→function registerPipelineCommands() {\n 794→  registerCommand(pipelineMeta, handlePipeline);\n 795→  registerCommand(bugfixMeta, handleBugfix);\n 796→  registerCommand(plannerMeta, handlePlanner);\n 797→  registerCommand(statusMeta, handleStatus);\n 798→  registerCommand(logsMeta, handleLogs);\n 799→  registerCommand(stopMeta, handleStop);\n 800→  registerCommand(planMeta, handlePlan);\n 801→  registerCommand(auditMeta, handleAudit);\n 802→  registerCommand(commitMeta, handleCommit);\n 803→  registerCommand(commitsMeta, handleCommits);\n 804→  // F-009: New commands\n 805→  registerCommand(cdMeta, handleCd);\n 806→  registerCommand(moreMeta, handleMore);\n 807→  // F-010: File Manager commands\n 808→  registerCommand(lsMeta, handleLs);\n 809→  registerCommand(treeMeta, handleTree);\n 810→  registerCommand(catMeta, handleCat);\n 811→  registerCommand(headMeta, handleHead);\n 812→  registerCommand(tailMeta, handleTail);\n 813→  registerCommand(findMeta, handleFind);\n 814→  registerCommand(uploadMeta, handleUpload);\n 815→  registerCommand(downloadMeta, handleDownload);\n 816→  // F-012: System Monitor commands\n 817→  registerCommand(sysinfoMeta, handleSysinfo);\n 818→  registerCommand(psMeta, handlePs);\n 819→  registerCommand(killMeta, handleKill);\n 820→  registerCommand(monitorMeta, handleMonitor);\n 821→  // F-013: Session and Context Manager commands\n 822→  registerCommand(historyMeta, handleHistory);\n 823→  registerCommand(aliasMeta, handleAlias);\n 824→  registerCommand(sessionsMeta, handleSessions);\n 825→  // F-014: Notification and Scheduled Tasks commands\n 826→  registerCommand(cronMeta, handleCron);\n 827→  registerCommand(jobsMeta, handleJobs);\n 828→  registerCommand(watchMeta, handleWatch);\n 829→}\n 830→\n 831→export async function createTelegramBot() {\n 832→  const bot = new Telegraf(config.telegramBotToken, {\n 833→    handlerTimeout: TELEGRAM_HANDLER_TIMEOUT_MS\n 834→  });\n 835→\n 836→  // F-013: Initialize session context service\n 837→  await sessionContextService.initSessionContext({ dataDir: config.sessionPersistenceDir });\n 838→  await aliasStore.initAliasStore({ persistencePath: config.aliasPersistencePath });\n 839→\n 840→  // F-013: Restore sessions from disk\n 841→  await sessionContextService.restoreSessions();\n 842→\n 843→  // F-013: Set up notification callback for session timeout\n 844→  sessionContextService.setNotificationCallback(async (sessionKey, userId) => {\n 845→    try {\n 846→      // Extract chat ID from session key (format: telegram:123456789)\n 847→      const chatId = sessionKey.replace('telegram:', '');\n 848→      await bot.telegram.sendMessage(chatId, '⏰ 会话因长时间未活动已超时，相关状态已清理。');\n 849→    } catch (error) {\n 850→      logger.warn({ sessionKey, userId, error: error.message }, 'Failed to send session timeout notification');\n 851→    }\n 852→  });\n 853→\n 854→  // F-013: Start timeout watcher\n 855→  sessionContextService.startTimeoutWatcher();\n 856→\n 857→  // F-014: Initialize scheduled task service\n 858→  scheduledTaskService.initScheduledTaskService({\n 859→    dataDir: config.systemMonitorDataDir,\n 860→    tasksFile: config.scheduledTasksPath,\n 861→    maxTasks: config.maxScheduledTasks\n 862→  });\n 863→\n 864→  // F-014: Set up task execution callback\n 865→  scheduledTaskService.setExecuteCallback(async ({ command, cwd, sessionId, userId }) => {\n 866→    try {\n 867→      return await executeCommand({\n 868→        command,\n 869→        cwd,\n 870→        sessionId,\n 871→        userId,\n 872→        skipConfirmation: true // Skip confirmation for scheduled tasks\n 873→      });\n 874→    } catch (error) {\n 875→      return {\n 876→        stdout: '',\n 877→        stderr: error.message,\n 878→        exitCode: 1,\n 879→        timedOut: false\n 880→      };\n 881→    }\n 882→  });\n 883→\n 884→  // F-014: Set up task notification callback\n 885→  scheduledTaskService.setNotificationCallback(async (chatId, task) => {\n 886→    try {\n 887→      const result = task.lastResult || {};\n 888→      const lines = [\n 889→        '⏰ *定时任务完成*',\n 890→        '',\n 891→        `任务ID: \\`${task.id.substring(0, 8)}...\\``,\n 892→        `命令: \\`${escapeMarkdownV2(task.command)}\\``,\n 893→        `执行时间: ${new Date(result.executedAt || Date.now()).toLocaleString()}`,\n 894→        '',\n 895→        `exitCode: ${result.exitCode}`,\n 896→        result.stdout ? `stdout:\\n${truncate(result.stdout, 500)}` : 'stdout: (empty)',\n 897→        result.stderr ? `stderr:\\n${escapeMarkdownV2(truncate(result.stderr, 500))}` : 'stderr: (empty)'\n 898→      ];\n 899→      await bot.telegram.sendMessage(chatId, lines.join('\\n'), { parse_mode: 'MarkdownV2' });\n 900→    } catch (error) {\n 901→      logger.warn({ taskId: task.id, error: error.message }, 'Failed to send task notification');\n 902→    }\n 903→  });\n 904→\n 905→  // F-014: Load and start scheduled tasks\n 906→  await scheduledTaskService.loadTasks();\n 907→  scheduledTaskService.startScheduler();\n 908→\n 909→  // F-014: Initialize file watcher service\n 910→  fileWatcherService.initFileWatcherService({\n 911→    dataDir: config.systemMonitorDataDir,\n 912→    watchersFile: config.fileWatchersPath,\n 913→    maxWatchers: config.maxFileWatchers,\n 914→    debounceMs: config.taskDebounceMs,\n 915→    allowedRoots: config.telegramFileAllowedRoots.length > 0\n 916→      ? config.telegramFileAllowedRoots\n 917→      : [process.cwd()]\n 918→  });\n 919→\n 920→  // F-014: Set up file watcher notification callback\n 921→  fileWatcherService.setNotificationCallback(async (chatId, watcher) => {\n 922→    try {\n 923→      const lines = [\n 924→        '📁 *文件变更检测*',\n 925→        '',\n 926→        `路径: \\`${escapeMarkdownV2(watcher.path)}\\``,\n 927→        `事件: ${watcher.eventType}`,\n 928→        `文件: ${watcher.filename || '(未知)'}`,\n 929→        `时间: ${new Date().toLocaleString()}`\n 930→      ];\n 931→      await bot.telegram.sendMessage(chatId, lines.join('\\n'), { parse_mode: 'MarkdownV2' });\n 932→    } catch (error) {\n 933→      logger.warn({ watcherId: watcher.id, error: error.message }, 'Failed to send file watcher notification');\n 934→    }\n 935→  });\n 936→\n 937→  // F-014: Restore file watchers\n 938→  await fileWatcherService.restoreWatches();\n 939→\n 940→  // Register pipeline commands\n 941→  registerPipelineCommands();\n 942→\n 943→  bot.catch(async (error, ctx) => {\n 944→    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n 945→    logger.error({ err: message, chatId: ctx?.chat?.id, updateType: ctx?.updateType }, 'Unhandled error while processing telegram update');\n 946→    try {\n 947→      if (ctx?.chat?.id) {\n 948→        await ctx.telegram.sendMessage(ctx.chat.id, '处理请求时出现异常，请重试一次。');\n 949→      }\n 950→    } catch (notifyError) {\n 951→      logger.warn({ err: notifyError instanceof Error ? notifyError.message : String(notifyError) }, 'Failed to notify user after unhandled telegram error');\n 952→    }\n 953→  });\n 954→\n 955→  bot.start(async (ctx) => {\n 956→    await ctx.reply('PrizmClaw 已启动。可直接聊天，也可用 /help 查看可用命令。');\n 957→  });\n 958→\n 959→  bot.help(async (ctx) => {\n 960→    const helpText = generateHelp();\n 961→    await ctx.reply(helpText);\n 962→  });\n 963→\n 964→  bot.command('reset', async (ctx) => {\n 965→    try {\n 966→      ensureAllowed(ctx);\n 967→      const sessionId = buildSessionId(ctx);\n 968→\n 969→      // F-011: Interrupt any running AI CLI task\n 970→      if (isAiCliRunning(sessionId)) {\n 971→        interruptAiCli(sessionId);\n 972→      }\n 973→\n 974→      resetSession({ channel: 'telegram', sessionId });\n 975→      await ctx.reply('已清空当前会话上下文。');\n 976→    } catch (error) {\n 977→      await ctx.reply(error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error));\n 978→    }\n 979→  });\n 980→\n 981→  bot.command('screenshot', async (ctx) => {\n 982→    try {\n 983→      ensureAllowed(ctx);\n 984→      await ctx.reply('正在获取截图。');\n 985→      const { buffer } = await captureScreenshot();\n 986→      await ctx.replyWithPhoto({ source: buffer }, { caption: '当前本地屏幕截图' });\n 987→    } catch (error) {\n 988→      const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n 989→      logger.error({ err: message }, 'Failed to capture screenshot in telegram');\n 990→      await ctx.reply(`截图失败：${message}`);\n 991→    }\n 992→  });\n 993→\n 994→  bot.command('exec', async (ctx) => {\n 995→    try {\n 996→      ensureAllowed(ctx);\n 997→      const payload = ctx.message.text.replace('/exec', '').trim();\n 998→      if (!payload) {\n 999→        await ctx.reply('请提供命令，例如 /exec pwd');\n1000→        return;\n1001→      }\n1002→\n1003→      const sessionId = buildSessionId(ctx);\n1004→      const userId = ctx.from?.id;\n1005→\n1006→      await ctx.reply('正在执行命令...');\n1007→      const result = await executeCommand({\n1008→        command: payload,\n1009→        sessionId,\n1010→        userId\n1011→      });\n1012→\n1013→      // Handle confirmation required\n1014→      if (result.needsConfirmation) {\n1015→        await ctx.reply(result.confirmationMessage);\n1016→        return;\n1017→      }\n1018→\n1019→      // Send output\n1020→      await replyLargeText(ctx, result.output);\n1021→\n1022→      // Indicate if more pages available\n1023→      if (result.hasMorePages) {\n1024→        await ctx.reply('📄 输出已截断。使用 /more 查看更多内容。');\n1025→      }\n1026→    } catch (error) {\n1027→      const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n1028→      logger.error({ err: message }, 'Failed to exec command in telegram');\n1029→      await ctx.reply(`执行失败：${message}`);\n1030→    }\n1031→  });\n1032→\n1033→  // F-009: /cd command handler\n1034→  bot.command('cd', async (ctx) => {\n1035→    try {\n1036→      ensureAllowed(ctx);\n1037→      const payload = ctx.message.text.replace('/cd', '').trim();\n1038→      const sessionId = buildSessionId(ctx);\n1039→\n1040→      await handleCd({\n1041→        ctx,\n1042→        reply: (msg) => ctx.reply(msg),\n1043→        params: {},\n1044→        userId: ctx.from?.id,\n1045→        sessionId,\n1046→        args: payload ? [payload] : []\n1047→      });\n1048→    } catch (error) {\n1049→      const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n1050→      logger.error({ err: message }, 'Failed to cd in telegram');\n1051→      await ctx.reply(`切换目录失败：${message}`);\n1052→    }\n1053→  });\n1054→\n1055→  // F-009: /more command handler\n1056→  bot.command('more', async (ctx) => {\n1057→    try {\n1058→      ensureAllowed(ctx);\n1059→      const sessionId = buildSessionId(ctx);\n1060→\n1061→      await handleMore({\n1062→        ctx,\n1063→        reply: (msg) => ctx.reply(msg),\n1064→        params: {},\n1065→        userId: ctx.from?.id,\n1066→        sessionId\n1067→      });\n1068→    } catch (error) {\n1069→      const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n1070→      logger.error({ err: message }, 'Failed to get more output in telegram');\n1071→      await ctx.reply(`获取更多输出失败：${message}`);\n1072→    }\n1073→  });\n1074→\n1075→  // T-100: Document upload handler for plan files\n1076→  bot.on('document', async (ctx) => {\n1077→    try {\n1078→      ensureAllowed(ctx);\n1079→\n1080→      const document = ctx.message?.document;\n1081→      if (!document) {\n1082→        return;\n1083→      }\n1084→\n1085→      // Check file extension\n1086→      const fileName = document.file_name || '';\n1087→      const ext = path.extname(fileName).toLowerCase();\n1088→\n1089→      if (ext !== '.json') {\n1090→        // Not a JSON file, ignore silently (other handlers may process it)\n1091→        return;\n1092→      }\n1093→\n1094→      // Check file size\n1095→      const fileSize = document.file_size || 0;\n1096→      if (fileSize > 1024 * 1024) { // 1MB limit\n1097→        await ctx.reply('❌ 文件过大，限制 1MB。');\n1098→        return;\n1099→      }\n1100→\n1101→      await ctx.reply('正在处理上传的计划文件...');\n1102→\n1103→      // Download file content\n1104→      const fileLink = await ctx.telegram.getFileLink(document.file_id);\n1105→      const fileUrl = fileLink.href || fileLink.toString();\n1106→\n1107→      const response = await fetch(fileUrl);\n1108→      if (!response.ok) {\n1109→        throw new Error(`下载文件失败: ${response.status}`);\n1110→      }\n1111→\n1112→      const content = await response.text();\n1113→\n1114→      // Validate and save using plan-ingestion-service\n1115→      const infraConfig = loadPipelineInfraConfig();\n1116→      const planService = createPlanIngestionService({ plansDir: infraConfig.plansDir });\n1117→\n1118→      const validationResult = planService.validate(content);\n1119→\n1120→      if (!validationResult.valid) {\n1121→        const errorMsg = planService.formatValidationErrors(validationResult.errors);\n1122→        await ctx.reply(errorMsg);\n1123→        return;\n1124→      }\n1125→\n1126→      // Save the plan\n1127→      const saveResult = await planService.save(\n1128→        validationResult.type,\n1129→        content,\n1130→        { uploadedBy: ctx.from?.id }\n1131→      );\n1132→\n1133→      if (!saveResult.success) {\n1134→        await ctx.reply('❌ 保存失败，请稍后重试。');\n1135→        return;\n1136→      }\n1137→\n1138→      // Set as current version\n1139→      await planService.setCurrent(validationResult.type, saveResult.version);\n1140→\n1141→      // Format success message\n1142→      const typeDisplay = validationResult.type === 'feature-list' ? '特性列表' : 'Bug修复列表';\n1143→      const summary = validationResult.summary;\n1144→\n1145→      await ctx.reply([\n1146→        `✅ ${typeDisplay}已保存并激活`,\n1147→        `版本: ${saveResult.version}`,\n1148→        `名称: ${summary?.name || '未知'}`,\n1149→        `项目数: ${summary?.itemCount || 0}`,\n1150→        '',\n1151→        summary?.statusBreakdown ? '状态分布:' : '',\n1152→        ...Object.entries(summary?.statusBreakdown || {}).map(([status, count]) => `  ${status}: ${count}`)\n1153→      ].filter(Boolean).join('\\n'));\n1154→\n1155→    } catch (error) {\n1156→      const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n1157→      logger.error({ err: message }, 'Failed to process document upload');\n1158→      await ctx.reply(`❌ 处理失败：${message}`);\n1159→    }\n1160→  });\n1161→\n1162→  bot.on('text', async (ctx) => {\n1163→    // Check for pipeline commands first\n1164→    const handled = await routeCommand(ctx);\n1165→    if (handled) {\n1166→      return;\n1167→    }\n1168→\n1169→    const sessionId = buildSessionId(ctx);\n1170→    const userId = ctx.from?.id;\n1171→\n1172→    // F-009: Direct exec mode - treat plain text as command when enabled\n1173→    if (config.directExecMode && config.enableSystemExec) {\n1174→      try {\n1175→        ensureAllowed(ctx);\n1176→        const command = ctx.message.text;\n1177→\n1178→        // Skip if it looks like a chat message (contains Chinese or Japanese characters, etc.)\n1179→        const isLikelyChat = /[\\u4e00-\\u9fff\\u3040-\\u309f\\u30a0-\\u30ff]/.test(command);\n1180→\n1181→        if (!isLikelyChat) {\n1182→          await ctx.reply('正在执行命令...');\n1183→          const result = await executeCommand({\n1184→            command,\n1185→            sessionId,\n1186→            userId\n1187→          });\n1188→\n1189→          if (result.needsConfirmation) {\n1190→            await ctx.reply(result.confirmationMessage);\n1191→            return;\n1192→          }\n1193→\n1194→          await replyLargeText(ctx, result.output);\n1195→\n1196→          if (result.hasMorePages) {\n1197→            await ctx.reply('📄 输出已截断。使用 /more 查看更多内容。');\n1198→          }\n1199→          return;\n1200→        }\n1201→      } catch (error) {\n1202→        const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n1203→        // If exec fails, fall through to chat mode\n1204→        logger.warn({ err: message }, 'Direct exec mode failed, falling back to chat');\n1205→      }\n1206→    }\n1207→\n1208→    // F-011: Check if AI CLI is already running\n1209→    if (isAiCliRunning(sessionId)) {\n1210→      await ctx.reply('⏳ 有任务正在执行，请等待完成或使用 /stop 中断。');\n1211→      return;\n1212→    }\n1213→\n1214→    let typingTimer = null;\n1215→\n1216→    try {\n1217→      ensureAllowed(ctx);\n1218→      await ctx.sendChatAction('typing');\n1219→\n1220→      const streamPublisher = createEditableStreamPublisher(ctx);\n1221→      typingTimer = setInterval(() => {\n1222→        ctx.sendChatAction('typing').catch(() => undefined);\n1223→      }, TYPING_INTERVAL_MS);\n1224→\n1225→      // F-011: Use ai-cli-service for execution with process tracking\n1226→      const sessionKey = `telegram:${sessionId}`;\n1227→\n1228→      // Append user message to session history\n1229→      sessionStore.append(sessionKey, 'user', ctx.message.text);\n1230→\n1231→      // Build prompt with context\n1232→      const prompt = sessionStore.toPrompt(sessionKey, 'telegram');\n1233→\n1234→      // Track last heartbeat message for updates\n1235→      /** @type {{ message_id: number } | null} */\n1236→      let lastHeartbeatMsg = null;\n1237→\n1238→      const result = await executeAiCli({\n1239→        sessionId,\n1240→        prompt,\n1241→        hooks: {\n1242→          onChunk: (text) => {\n1243→            streamPublisher.push(text);\n1244→          },\n1245→          onHeartbeat: config.aiCliEnableHeartbeat ? (info) => {\n1246→            // Send/update heartbeat progress message\n1247→            const elapsedSec = Math.floor(info.elapsedMs / 1000);\n1248→            const progressText = `⏳ 任务执行中... (${elapsedSec}s, ${Math.floor(info.stdoutBytes / 1024)}KB)`;\n1249→\n1250→            // Don't await - fire and forget\n1251→            if (lastHeartbeatMsg) {\n1252→              ctx.telegram.editMessageText(ctx.chat.id, lastHeartbeatMsg.message_id, undefined, progressText)\n1253→                .catch(() => {});\n1254→            } else {\n1255→              ctx.reply(progressText)\n1256→                .then((msg) => { lastHeartbeatMsg = msg; })\n1257→                .catch(() => {});\n1258→            }\n1259→          } : undefined,\n1260→          onStatus: (status) => {\n1261→            if (status === 'running') {\n1262→              ctx.sendChatAction('typing').catch(() => undefined);\n1263→            }\n1264→          }\n1265→        }\n1266→      });\n1267→\n1268→      // Delete heartbeat message if exists\n1269→      if (lastHeartbeatMsg) {\n1270→        ctx.telegram.deleteMessage(ctx.chat.id, lastHeartbeatMsg.message_id).catch(() => {});\n1271→      }\n1272→\n1273→      // Append assistant reply to session history\n1274→      sessionStore.append(sessionKey, 'assistant', result.output);\n1275→\n1276→      // F-011: Format output with MarkdownV2\n1277→      const formattedOutput = convertToMarkdownV2(result.output);\n1278→\n1279→      // Handle result states\n1280→      if (result.interrupted) {\n1281→        await ctx.reply('⏹️ 任务已被中断。');\n1282→      } else if (result.timedOut) {\n1283→        await ctx.reply(`⏰ 任务执行超时。\\n建议：使用 /stop 中断或增加 REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS 配置。`);\n1284→      }\n1285→\n1286→      // Extract file markers and send\n1287→      const { fileRefs, cleanedText } = extractFileMarkers(result.output);\n1288→      logger.info({ sessionId, fileRefsCount: fileRefs.length, fileRefs }, 'Parsed file markers from assistant reply');\n1289→      const finalText = cleanedText || (fileRefs.length > 0 ? '已执行，正在发送文件。' : '已执行。');\n1290→\n1291→      streamPublisher.setFinalText(finalText);\n1292→      const streamed = await streamPublisher.finish();\n1293→      if (streamed.outputLength === 0) {\n1294→        await replyLargeText(ctx, finalText);\n1295→      }\n1296→\n1297→      if (fileRefs.length > 0) {\n1298→        const fileSendResults = await replyFiles(ctx, fileRefs);\n1299→        const failed = fileSendResults.filter((item) => !item.sent);\n1300→\n1301→        if (failed.length === 0) {\n1302→          await safeReply(ctx, `已发送 ${fileSendResults.length} 个文件。`);\n1303→        } else {\n1304→          const failedList = failed\n1305→            .map((item) => {\n1306→              const reason =\n1307→                item.reason === 'relative_path_not_allowed'\n1308→                  ? '仅允许绝对路径，拒绝相对路径（请使用 SEND_FILE:/var/folders/.../xxx.png）'\n1309→                  : item.reason === 'not_found'\n1310→                    ? '文件不存在或不可访问（建议返回绝对路径，例如 SEND_FILE:/var/folders/.../xxx.png）'\n1311→                    : item.reason;\n1312→              const tried = Array.isArray(item.triedPaths) && item.triedPaths.length > 0 ? `；尝试路径：${item.triedPaths.join(' | ')}` : '';\n1313→              return `- SEND_FILE:${item.fileRef}${reason ? `（${reason}）` : ''}${tried}`;\n1314→            })\n1315→            .join('\\n');\n1316→          await safeReply(ctx, `以下文件发送失败，已附回原始引用：\\n${failedList}`);\n1317→          logger.warn({ sessionId, failed }, 'Some files failed to send to telegram');\n1318→        }\n1319→      }\n1320→    } catch (error) {\n1321→      const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n1322→      logger.error({ err: message, sessionId }, 'Failed to process telegram message');\n1323→      await safeReply(ctx, `处理失败：${message}`);\n1324→    } finally {\n1325→      if (typingTimer) {\n1326→        clearInterval(typingTimer);\n1327→      }\n1328→    }\n1329→  });\n1330→\n1331→  return bot;\n1332→}\n1333→\n1334→```\n1335→\n1336→### src/bot/commands/index.js (193 lines)\n1337→\n1338→```js\n1339→/**\n1340→ * Command Router\n1341→ * Main entry point for command routing and dispatch.\n1342→ */\n1343→\n1344→import { parseCommand } from './parser.js';\n1345→import { getCommand, getAliasMap, registerCommand } from './registry.js';\n1346→import { validateCommand } from './validator.js';\n1347→import { formatError, formatValidationErrors, ErrorCodes } from './formatter.js';\n1348→import { isAllowedUser } from '../../security/guard.js';\n1349→import { checkCommandPermission, getUserRole } from '../../security/permission-guard.js';\n1350→import { logAuditEntry } from '../../services/audit-log-service.js';\n1351→import { aliasStore } from '../../services/alias-store.js';\n1352→import { sessionStore } from '../../services/session-store.js';\n1353→\n1354→/**\n1355→ * @typedef {import('./parser.js').ParsedCommand} ParsedCommand\n1356→ * @typedef {import('./registry.js').CommandMeta} CommandMeta\n1357→ * @typedef {import('./registry.js').CommandEntry} CommandEntry\n1358→ */\n1359→\n1360→/**\n1361→ * Build session ID from context.\n1362→ * @param {Object} ctx - Telegraf context\n1363→ * @returns {string} Session ID\n1364→ */\n1365→function buildSessionId(ctx) {\n1366→  return String(ctx.chat.id);\n1367→}\n1368→\n1369→/**\n1370→ * Route and dispatch a command from Telegram context.\n1371→ * @param {Object} ctx - Telegraf context\n1372→ * @returns {Promise<boolean>} True if command was handled\n1373→ */\n1374→export async function routeCommand(ctx) {\n1375→  let text = ctx.message?.text;\n1376→\n1377→  if (!text || !text.startsWith('/')) {\n1378→    return false;\n1379→  }\n1380→\n1381→  // Authorization check\n1382→  const userId = ctx.from?.id;\n1383→  if (!isAuthorized(userId)) {\n1384→    await ctx.reply(formatErrorResponse(formatError(ErrorCodes.UNAUTHORIZED)));\n1385→    return true;\n1386→  }\n1387→\n1388→  const sessionId = buildSessionId(ctx);\n1389→  const userIdStr = String(userId);\n1390→\n1391→  // F-013: Touch session on each command\n1392→  sessionStore.touchSession(sessionId, userIdStr);\n1393→\n1394→  // F-013: Resolve alias if the command name is an alias\n1395→  const commandMatch = text.match(/^\\/(\\S+)/);\n1396→  if (commandMatch) {\n1397→    const potentialAlias = commandMatch[1].toLowerCase();\n1398→    const resolvedCommand = aliasStore.resolveAlias(userIdStr, potentialAlias);\n1399→    if (resolvedCommand) {\n1400→      // Replace the alias with the resolved command\n1401→      const args = text.slice(commandMatch[0].length);\n1402→      text = `/${resolvedCommand}${args}`;\n1403→    }\n1404→  }\n1405→\n1406→  // Parse command\n1407→  const aliasMap = getAliasMap();\n1408→  const parsed = parseCommand(text, aliasMap);\n1409→\n1410→  if (!parsed) {\n1411→    await ctx.reply('无法解析命令。');\n1412→    return true;\n1413→  }\n1414→\n1415→  // Lookup command\n1416→  const entry = getCommand(parsed.command);\n1417→\n1418→  if (!entry) {\n1419→    await ctx.reply(formatErrorResponse(formatError(ErrorCodes.UNKNOWN_COMMAND, { command: parsed.command })));\n1420→    return true;\n1421→  }\n1422→\n1423→  const { meta, handler } = entry;\n1424→\n1425→  // T-101: Permission check\n1426→  const commandName = meta.name;\n1427→  const permResult = checkCommandPermission(userId, commandName);\n1428→\n1429→  if (!permResult.allowed) {\n1430→    // Log denied access\n1431→    await logAuditEntry({\n1432→      userId,\n1433→      action: commandName,\n1434→      params: {},\n1435→      result: 'denied',\n1436→      reason: permResult.reason\n1437→    });\n1438→\n1439→    await ctx.reply(`⛔ ${permResult.reason}`);\n1440→    return true;\n1441→  }\n1442→\n1443→  // Validate command\n1444→  const validation = validateCommand(parsed, meta);\n1445→\n1446→  if (!validation.valid) {\n1447→    const errorMsg = formatValidationErrors(validation.errors, meta.usage);\n1448→    await ctx.reply(errorMsg);\n1449→    return true;\n1450→  }\n1451→\n1452→  // Create handler context\n1453→  const handlerContext = {\n1454→    ctx,\n1455→    parsed,\n1456→    meta,\n1457→    params: validation.normalized || {},\n1458→    userId,\n1459→    userRole: getUserRole(userId),\n1460→    sessionId,\n1461→    requiresConfirmation: permResult.requiresConfirmation,\n1462→    reply: async (text) => ctx.reply(text),\n1463→    replyFile: async (content, filename) => {\n1464→      // Will be implemented with proper file handling\n1465→      await ctx.replyWithDocument({ source: Buffer.from(content), filename });\n1466→    },\n1467→    args: parsed.args || []\n1468→  };\n1469→\n1470→  // Dispatch to handler\n1471→  try {\n1472→    await handler(handlerContext);\n1473→  } catch (error) {\n1474→    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n1475→    await ctx.reply(formatErrorResponse(formatError(ErrorCodes.INTERNAL_ERROR, { reason: message })));\n1476→  }\n1477→\n1478→  return true;\n1479→}\n1480→\n1481→/**\n1482→ * Check if user is authorized.\n1483→ * @param {number|string|undefined} userId - User ID\n1484→ * @returns {boolean} True if authorized\n1485→ */\n1486→function isAuthorized(userId) {\n1487→  return isAllowedUser(userId);\n1488→}\n1489→\n1490→/**\n1491→ * Format error response for display.\n1492→ * @param {Object} error - Error object\n1493→ * @returns {string} Formatted error\n1494→ */\n1495→function formatErrorResponse(error) {\n1496→  const lines = [`❌ ${error.message}`];\n1497→\n1498→  if (error.suggestion) {\n1499→    lines.push(`💡 ${error.suggestion}`);\n1500→  }\n1501→\n1502→  if (error.usage) {\n1503→    lines.push(`用法: ${error.usage}`);\n1504→  }\n1505→\n1506→  return lines.join('\\n');\n1507→}\n1508→\n1509→/**\n1510→ * Register all default commands.\n1511→ */\n1512→export function registerDefaultCommands() {\n1513→  // Commands will be registered by individual handlers\n1514→  // This is called during initialization\n1515→}\n1516→\n1517→/**\n1518→ * Create middleware for command routing.\n1519→ * @returns {Function} Middleware function\n1520→ */\n1521→export function createCommandMiddleware() {\n1522→  return async (ctx, next) => {\n1523→    const handled = await routeCommand(ctx);\n1524→    if (!handled) {\n1525→      return next();\n1526→    }\n1527→  };\n1528→}\n1529→\n1530→// Re-export for convenience\n1531→export { registerCommand, getCommand, getAliasMap };\n1532→\n1533→```\n1534→\n1535→### src/bot/commands/parser.js (94 lines)\n1536→\n1537→```js\n1538→/**\n1539→ * Command Parser\n1540→ * Parses Telegram message text into structured ParsedCommand object.\n1541→ */\n1542→\n1543→/**\n1544→ * @typedef {Object} ParsedCommand\n1545→ * @property {string} command - The command name (e.g., \"pipeline\")\n1546→ * @property {string} [subcommand] - Optional subcommand (e.g., \"run\")\n1547→ * @property {string[]} args - Positional arguments\n1548→ * @property {Record<string, string>} options - Key-value options (--key=value)\n1549→ * @property {string} raw - Original message text\n1550→ */\n1551→\n1552→/**\n1553→ * Parse Telegram message text into a structured command object.\n1554→ * @param {string} text - The message text to parse\n1555→ * @param {Object} [aliasMap={}] - Map of aliases to command names\n1556→ * @returns {ParsedCommand | null} Parsed command or null if not a command\n1557→ */\n1558→export function parseCommand(text, aliasMap = {}) {\n1559→  if (!text || typeof text !== 'string') {\n1560→    return null;\n1561→  }\n1562→\n1563→  const trimmed = text.trim();\n1564→\n1565→  // Must start with /\n1566→  if (!trimmed.startsWith('/')) {\n1567→    return null;\n1568→  }\n1569→\n1570→  // Extract command (first token after /)\n1571→  const tokens = trimmed.slice(1).split(/\\s+/);\n1572→  if (tokens.length === 0 || !tokens[0]) {\n1573→    return null;\n1574→  }\n1575→\n1576→  let command = tokens[0].toLowerCase();\n1577→  const rest = tokens.slice(1);\n1578→\n1579→  // Handle @bot suffix (e.g., /command@mybot)\n1580→  const atIndex = command.indexOf('@');\n1581→  if (atIndex !== -1) {\n1582→    command = command.slice(0, atIndex);\n1583→  }\n1584→\n1585→  // Apply alias mapping\n1586→  if (aliasMap[command]) {\n1587→    command = aliasMap[command];\n1588→  }\n1589→\n1590→  const args = [];\n1591→  /** @type {Record<string, string>} */\n1592→  const options = {};\n1593→  let subcommand = undefined;\n1594→\n1595→  for (const token of rest) {\n1596→    // Parse --key=value options\n1597→    if (token.startsWith('--')) {\n1598→      const optionText = token.slice(2);\n1599→      const eqIndex = optionText.indexOf('=');\n1600→      if (eqIndex !== -1) {\n1601→        const key = optionText.slice(0, eqIndex).toLowerCase();\n1602→        const value = optionText.slice(eqIndex + 1);\n1603→        options[key] = value;\n1604→      } else {\n1605→        // Boolean flag --flag\n1606→        options[optionText.toLowerCase()] = 'true';\n1607→      }\n1608→    } else if (token.includes('=')) {\n1609→      // Parse key=value (without --)\n1610→      const eqIndex = token.indexOf('=');\n1611→      const key = token.slice(0, eqIndex).toLowerCase();\n1612→      const value = token.slice(eqIndex + 1);\n1613→      options[key] = value;\n1614→    } else if (subcommand === undefined && !token.startsWith('-') && args.length === 0) {\n1615→      // First non-option token is subcommand if it looks like one\n1616→      // This will be validated by the registry\n1617→      subcommand = token.toLowerCase();\n1618→    } else {\n1619→      // Positional argument\n1620→      args.push(token);\n1621→    }\n1622→  }\n1623→\n1624→  return {\n1625→    command,\n1626→    subcommand,\n1627→    args,\n1628→    options,\n1629→    raw: text\n1630→  };\n1631→}\n1632→\n1633→```\n1634→\n1635→### src/bot/commands/registry.js (220 lines)\n1636→\n1637→```js\n1638→/**\n1639→ * Command Registry\n1640→ * Manages command registration, lookup, and metadata.\n1641→ */\n1642→\n1643→/**\n1644→ * @typedef {Object} ParamMeta\n1645→ * @property {string} name - Parameter name\n1646→ * @property {boolean} required - Whether the parameter is required\n1647→ * @property {string} description - Parameter description\n1648→ * @property {string} [type] - Parameter type (string, number, enum)\n1649→ * @property {string[]} [enum] - Allowed values for enum type\n1650→ * @property {*} [default] - Default value\n1651→ */\n1652→\n1653→/**\n1654→ * @typedef {Object} SubcommandMeta\n1655→ * @property {string} name - Subcommand name\n1656→ * @property {string} description - Subcommand description\n1657→ * @property {ParamMeta[]} [params] - Subcommand parameters\n1658→ */\n1659→\n1660→/**\n1661→ * @typedef {Object} CommandMeta\n1662→ * @property {string} name - Command name\n1663→ * @property {string[]} [aliases] - Command aliases\n1664→ * @property {string} description - Command description\n1665→ * @property {string} usage - Usage example\n1666→ * @property {string[]} [examples] - Usage examples\n1667→ * @property {SubcommandMeta[]} [subcommands] - Available subcommands\n1668→ * @property {ParamMeta[]} [params] - Command parameters\n1669→ * @property {boolean} requiresAuth - Whether authorization is required\n1670→ * @property {string} [minRole] - Minimum required role (viewer, operator, admin)\n1671→ * @property {boolean} [requiresConfirmation] - Whether confirmation is required for high-risk commands\n1672→ * @property {string} helpText - Help text for the command\n1673→ */\n1674→\n1675→/**\n1676→ * @typedef {Object} CommandEntry\n1677→ * @property {CommandMeta} meta - Command metadata\n1678→ * @property {Function} handler - Command handler function\n1679→ */\n1680→\n1681→/**\n1682→ * @typedef {import('./parser.js').ParsedCommand} ParsedCommand\n1683→ */\n1684→\n1685→// Internal registry storage\n1686→const commands = new Map();\n1687→const aliasToCommand = new Map();\n1688→\n1689→/**\n1690→ * Register a command with its metadata and handler.\n1691→ * @param {CommandMeta} meta - Command metadata\n1692→ * @param {Function} handler - Command handler function\n1693→ * @throws {Error} If command already registered\n1694→ */\n1695→export function registerCommand(meta, handler) {\n1696→  if (!meta || !meta.name) {\n1697→    throw new Error('Command meta must have a name');\n1698→  }\n1699→\n1700→  // Normalize meta with lowercase name\n1701→  const normalizedMeta = {\n1702→    ...meta,\n1703→    name: meta.name.toLowerCase()\n1704→  };\n1705→  const name = normalizedMeta.name;\n1706→\n1707→  if (commands.has(name)) {\n1708→    throw new Error(`Command \"${name}\" is already registered`);\n1709→  }\n1710→\n1711→  // Register command\n1712→  commands.set(name, { meta: normalizedMeta, handler });\n1713→\n1714→  // Register aliases\n1715→  if (meta.aliases && Array.isArray(meta.aliases)) {\n1716→    for (const alias of meta.aliases) {\n1717→      const aliasLower = alias.toLowerCase();\n1718→      if (aliasToCommand.has(aliasLower)) {\n1719→        throw new Error(`Alias \"${alias}\" is already registered`);\n1720→      }\n1721→      aliasToCommand.set(aliasLower, name);\n1722→    }\n1723→  }\n1724→}\n1725→\n1726→/**\n1727→ * Get a command entry by name or alias.\n1728→ * @param {string} name - Command name or alias\n1729→ * @returns {CommandEntry | null} Command entry or null\n1730→ */\n1731→export function getCommand(name) {\n1732→  if (!name || typeof name !== 'string') {\n1733→    return null;\n1734→  }\n1735→\n1736→  const nameLower = name.toLowerCase();\n1737→\n1738→  // Try direct lookup\n1739→  if (commands.has(nameLower)) {\n1740→    return commands.get(nameLower);\n1741→  }\n1742→\n1743→  // Try alias lookup\n1744→  const resolvedName = aliasToCommand.get(nameLower);\n1745→  if (resolvedName && commands.has(resolvedName)) {\n1746→    return commands.get(resolvedName);\n1747→  }\n1748→\n1749→  return null;\n1750→}\n1751→\n1752→/**\n1753→ * Check if a name is a registered alias.\n1754→ * @param {string} name - Name to check\n1755→ * @returns {boolean} True if name is an alias\n1756→ */\n1757→export function isAlias(name) {\n1758→  if (!name || typeof name !== 'string') {\n1759→    return false;\n1760→  }\n1761→  return aliasToCommand.has(name.toLowerCase());\n1762→}\n1763→\n1764→/**\n1765→ * Get all registered commands.\n1766→ * @returns {CommandEntry[]} All command entries\n1767→ */\n1768→export function getAllCommands() {\n1769→  return Array.from(commands.values());\n1770→}\n1771→\n1772→/**\n1773→ * Generate help text for a specific command or all commands.\n1774→ * @param {string} [commandName] - Optional command name for specific help\n1775→ * @returns {string} Help text\n1776→ */\n1777→export function getHelpText(commandName) {\n1778→  if (commandName) {\n1779→    const entry = getCommand(commandName);\n1780→    if (!entry) {\n1781→      return `未知命令 '${commandName}'。输入 /help 查看可用命令。`;\n1782→    }\n1783→    return formatCommandHelp(entry.meta);\n1784→  }\n1785→\n1786→  // Generate general help\n1787→  const commandList = getAllCommands()\n1788→    .map((entry) => {\n1789→      const aliases = entry.meta.aliases?.length ? ` (${entry.meta.aliases.map((a) => `/${a}`).join(', ')})` : '';\n1790→      return `/${entry.meta.name}${aliases} - ${entry.meta.description}`;\n1791→    })\n1792→    .sort();\n1793→\n1794→  return `可用命令：\\n\\n${commandList.join('\\n')}`;\n1795→}\n1796→\n1797→/**\n1798→ * Format detailed help for a single command.\n1799→ * @param {CommandMeta} meta - Command metadata\n1800→ * @returns {string} Formatted help text\n1801→ */\n1802→function formatCommandHelp(meta) {\n1803→  const lines = [`/${meta.name} - ${meta.description}`];\n1804→\n1805→  if (meta.aliases?.length) {\n1806→    lines.push(`别名: ${meta.aliases.map((a) => `/${a}`).join(', ')}`);\n1807→  }\n1808→\n1809→  if (meta.usage) {\n1810→    lines.push(`用法: ${meta.usage}`);\n1811→  }\n1812→\n1813→  if (meta.subcommands?.length) {\n1814→    lines.push('\\n子命令:');\n1815→    for (const sub of meta.subcommands) {\n1816→      lines.push(`  ${sub.name} - ${sub.description}`);\n1817→    }\n1818→  }\n1819→\n1820→  if (meta.params?.length) {\n1821→    lines.push('\\n参数:');\n1822→    for (const param of meta.params) {\n1823→      const required = param.required ? '(必填)' : '(可选)';\n1824→      lines.push(`  ${param.name} ${required} - ${param.description}`);\n1825→    }\n1826→  }\n1827→\n1828→  if (meta.examples?.length) {\n1829→    lines.push('\\n示例:');\n1830→    for (const example of meta.examples) {\n1831→      lines.push(`  ${example}`);\n1832→    }\n1833→  }\n1834→\n1835→  return lines.join('\\n');\n1836→}\n1837→\n1838→/**\n1839→ * Clear the registry (for testing).\n1840→ */\n1841→export function clearRegistry() {\n1842→  commands.clear();\n1843→  aliasToCommand.clear();\n1844→}\n1845→\n1846→/**\n1847→ * Get the alias map for parser usage.\n1848→ * @returns {Record<string, string>} Alias to command name mapping\n1849→ */\n1850→export function getAliasMap() {\n1851→  /** @type {Record<string, string>} */\n1852→  const map = {};\n1853→  for (const [alias, command] of aliasToCommand) {\n1854→    map[alias] = command;\n1855→  }\n1856→  return map;\n1857→}\n1858→\n1859→```\n1860→\n1861→### src/bot/commands/validator.js (223 lines)\n1862→\n1863→```js\n1864→/**\n1865→ * Command Validator\n1866→ * Validates command parameters and generates error messages.\n1867→ */\n1868→\n1869→/**\n1870→ * @typedef {Object} ValidationError\n1871→ * @property {string} param - Parameter name\n1872→ * @property {string} message - Error message\n1873→ * @property {string} [suggestion] - Correction suggestion\n1874→ */\n1875→\n1876→/**\n1877→ * @typedef {Object} ValidationResult\n1878→ * @property {boolean} valid - Whether validation passed\n1879→ * @property {ValidationError[]} errors - Validation errors\n1880→ * @property {Record<string, *>} [normalized] - Normalized parameters\n1881→ */\n1882→\n1883→/**\n1884→ * @typedef {import('./parser.js').ParsedCommand} ParsedCommand\n1885→ * @typedef {import('./registry.js').CommandMeta} CommandMeta\n1886→ * @typedef {import('./registry.js').ParamMeta} ParamMeta\n1887→ * @typedef {import('./registry.js').SubcommandMeta} SubcommandMeta\n1888→ */\n1889→\n1890→/**\n1891→ * Validate a parsed command against its metadata.\n1892→ * @param {ParsedCommand} parsed - Parsed command\n1893→ * @param {CommandMeta} meta - Command metadata\n1894→ * @returns {ValidationResult} Validation result\n1895→ */\n1896→export function validateCommand(parsed, meta) {\n1897→  const errors = [];\n1898→  /** @type {Record<string, *>} */\n1899→  const normalized = { ...parsed.options };\n1900→\n1901→  // Validate subcommand if command has subcommands\n1902→  if (meta.subcommands?.length) {\n1903→    const validSubcommands = meta.subcommands.map((s) => s.name);\n1904→    if (parsed.subcommand && !validSubcommands.includes(parsed.subcommand)) {\n1905→      errors.push({\n1906→        param: 'subcommand',\n1907→        message: `未知子命令 '${parsed.subcommand}'`,\n1908→        suggestion: `可用子命令: ${validSubcommands.join(', ')}`\n1909→      });\n1910→    }\n1911→  }\n1912→\n1913→  // Get applicable params\n1914→  const params = getParamsForSubcommand(meta, parsed.subcommand);\n1915→\n1916→  // Validate parameters\n1917→  for (let i = 0; i < params.length; i++) {\n1918→    const param = params[i];\n1919→    const value = getParamValue(parsed, param.name, meta, i);\n1920→    const validationResult = validateParam(param, value);\n1921→\n1922→    if (!validationResult.valid) {\n1923→      errors.push(validationResult.error);\n1924→    } else if (validationResult.value !== undefined) {\n1925→      normalized[param.name] = validationResult.value;\n1926→    }\n1927→  }\n1928→\n1929→  // Add positional args to normalized\n1930→  if (parsed.args.length > 0) {\n1931→    normalized._args = parsed.args;\n1932→  }\n1933→\n1934→  return {\n1935→    valid: errors.length === 0,\n1936→    errors,\n1937→    normalized: errors.length === 0 ? normalized : undefined\n1938→  };\n1939→}\n1940→\n1941→/**\n1942→ * Get parameters applicable to a subcommand.\n1943→ * @param {CommandMeta} meta - Command metadata\n1944→ * @param {string|undefined} subcommand - Subcommand name\n1945→ * @returns {ParamMeta[]} Parameters\n1946→ */\n1947→function getParamsForSubcommand(meta, subcommand) {\n1948→  const params = [...(meta.params || [])];\n1949→\n1950→  // Add subcommand-specific params\n1951→  if (subcommand && meta.subcommands) {\n1952→    const subMeta = meta.subcommands.find((s) => s.name === subcommand);\n1953→    if (subMeta?.params) {\n1954→      params.push(...subMeta.params);\n1955→    }\n1956→  }\n1957→\n1958→  return params;\n1959→}\n1960→\n1961→/**\n1962→ * Get parameter value from parsed command.\n1963→ * @param {ParsedCommand} parsed - Parsed command\n1964→ * @param {string} paramName - Parameter name\n1965→ * @param {CommandMeta} meta - Command metadata\n1966→ * @param {number} paramIndex - Index of parameter in params array\n1967→ * @returns {string|undefined} Parameter value\n1968→ */\n1969→function getParamValue(parsed, paramName, meta, paramIndex) {\n1970→  // Check options first (explicit --key=value takes precedence)\n1971→  if (parsed.options[paramName] !== undefined) {\n1972→    return parsed.options[paramName];\n1973→  }\n1974→\n1975→  // Build positional args list\n1976→  // If command has no subcommands, parsed.subcommand should be treated as first positional arg\n1977→  const hasSubcommands = meta.subcommands && meta.subcommands.length > 0;\n1978→  const positionalArgs = [];\n1979→\n1980→  if (!hasSubcommands && parsed.subcommand !== undefined) {\n1981→    // F002-CRIT-001: Treat subcommand as first positional param when command has no subcommands\n1982→    positionalArgs.push(parsed.subcommand);\n1983→  }\n1984→\n1985→  // Add remaining args\n1986→  positionalArgs.push(...parsed.args);\n1987→\n1988→  // Map positional arg by index\n1989→  if (paramIndex !== undefined && positionalArgs[paramIndex] !== undefined) {\n1990→    return positionalArgs[paramIndex];\n1991→  }\n1992→\n1993→  return undefined;\n1994→}\n1995→\n1996→/**\n1997→ * Validate a single parameter.\n1998→ * @param {ParamMeta} param - Parameter metadata\n1999→ * @param {string|undefined} value - Parameter value\n2000→ * @returns {{valid: boolean, error?: ValidationError, value?: *}}"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_ytOeuPPPaoMyUkPYR8DqfePP","__timestamp":"2026-03-19T17:12:53.95